WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
-== [ www.OpenSubtitles.org ] ==-

2
00:00:32.913 --> 00:00:35.939
The world is changed.

3
00:00:36.116 --> 00:00:39.142
I feel it in the water.

4
00:00:39.920 --> 00:00:42.821
I feel it in the earth.

5
00:00:44.391 --> 00:00:47.417
I smell it in the air.

6
00:00:47.794 --> 00:00:49.694
Much that once was...

7
00:00:49.896 --> 00:00:51.454
...is lost.

8
00:00:52.165 --> 00:00:55.191
For none now live who remember it.

9
00:01:08.115 --> 00:01:12.484
It began with the forging
of the Great Rings.

10
00:01:12.686 --> 00:01:14.586
Three were given to the Elves:

11
00:01:14.755 --> 00:01:18.555
Immortal. wisest and fairest
of all beings.

12
00:01:19.626 --> 00:01:21.685
Seven to the Dwarf-lords:

13
00:01:22.462 --> 00:01:26.865
Great miners and craftsmen
of the mountain halls.

14
00:01:27.334 --> 00:01:28.562
And nine...

15
00:01:28.769 --> 00:01:31.795
...nine rings were gifted
to the race of Men...

16
00:01:32.005 --> 00:01:35.839
...who. above all else. desire power.

17
00:01:36.977 --> 00:01:42.176
For within these rings was bound
the strength and will to govern each race.

18
00:01:43.683 --> 00:01:46.846
But they were all of them deceived.

19
00:01:47.087 --> 00:01:49.180
For another ring was made.

20
00:01:50.023 --> 00:01:53.584
In the land of Mordor.
in the fires of Mount Doom...

21
00:01:54.027 --> 00:01:58.487
...the Dark Lord Sauron forged
in secret a Master Ring...

22
00:01:58.698 --> 00:02:00.723
...to control all others.

23
00:02:00.934 --> 00:02:04.893
And into this Ring he poured
his cruelty. his malice...

24
00:02:05.105 --> 00:02:09.303
...and his will to dominate all life.

25
00:02:10.277 --> 00:02:14.179
One Ring to rule them all.

26
00:02:15.015 --> 00:02:16.676
One by one...

27
00:02:16.883 --> 00:02:21.547
...the Free Lands of Middle-earth
fell to the power of the Ring.

28
00:02:21.755 --> 00:02:24.781
But there were some who resisted.

29
00:02:25.258 --> 00:02:29.922
A Last Alliance of Men and Elves
marched against the armies of Mordor.

30
00:02:30.130 --> 00:02:34.760
And on the slopes of Mount Doom. they
fought for the freedom of Middle-earth.

31
00:03:05.098 --> 00:03:07.692
Victory was near.

32
00:03:12.472 --> 00:03:14.235
But the power of the Ring...

33
00:03:15.075 --> 00:03:16.474
...could not be undone.

34
00:03:41.101 --> 00:03:43.001
It was in this moment...

35
00:03:43.203 --> 00:03:45.603
...when all hope had faded...

36
00:03:45.805 --> 00:03:49.901
...that Isildur. son of the king.
took up his father's sword.

37
00:04:21.007 --> 00:04:27.503
Sauron. the enemy of the Free Peoples
of Middle-earth. was defeated.

38
00:04:34.387 --> 00:04:36.548
The Ring passed to Isildur...

39
00:04:36.756 --> 00:04:40.988
...who had this one chance
to destroy evil forever.

40
00:04:41.695 --> 00:04:43.822
But the hearts of Men...

41
00:04:44.030 --> 00:04:46.521
...are easily corrupted.

42
00:04:46.766 --> 00:04:51.396
And the Ring of Power
has a will of its own.

43
00:04:59.813 --> 00:05:03.909
It betrayed Isildur to his death.

44
00:05:06.086 --> 00:05:09.954
And some things
that should not have been forgotten...

45
00:05:10.156 --> 00:05:12.488
...were lost.

46
00:05:13.360 --> 00:05:15.555
History became legend...

47
00:05:15.762 --> 00:05:17.753
...legend became myth.

48
00:05:17.964 --> 00:05:20.831
And for
two and a half thousand years...

49
00:05:21.034 --> 00:05:24.731
...the Ring passed
out of all knowledge.

50
00:05:25.372 --> 00:05:28.170
Until. when chance came...

51
00:05:28.842 --> 00:05:31.970
...it ensnared a new bearer.

52
00:05:33.346 --> 00:05:38.215
My precious.

53
00:05:38.451 --> 00:05:40.976
The Ring came to the creature
Gollum...

54
00:05:41.154 --> 00:05:45.090
...who took it deep into the tunnels
of the Misty Mountains.

55
00:05:45.392 --> 00:05:48.259
And there it consumed him.

56
00:05:48.461 --> 00:05:50.486
It came to me.

57
00:05:50.697 --> 00:05:55.134
My own. My love. My own.

58
00:05:55.335 --> 00:06:00.034
My precious.

59
00:06:03.677 --> 00:06:07.113
The Ring brought to Gollum
unnatural long life.

60
00:06:07.313 --> 00:06:11.147
For 500 years it poisoned his mind.

61
00:06:11.351 --> 00:06:15.947
And in the gloom of Gollum's cave.
it waited.

62
00:06:16.156 --> 00:06:19.387
Darkness crept back
into the forests of the world.

63
00:06:19.659 --> 00:06:22.492
Rumor grew of a shadow in the East...

64
00:06:22.696 --> 00:06:25.494
...whispers of a nameless fear.

65
00:06:25.699 --> 00:06:28.998
And the Ring of Power perceived...

66
00:06:29.202 --> 00:06:32.000
...its time had now come.

67
00:06:34.441 --> 00:06:37.069
It abandoned Gollum.

68
00:06:37.777 --> 00:06:42.237
But something happened then
the Ring did not intend.

69
00:06:43.083 --> 00:06:47.679
It was picked up by the most unlikely
creature imaginable.

70
00:06:47.887 --> 00:06:48.945
What's this?

71
00:06:49.155 --> 00:06:50.588
A Hobbit.

72
00:06:50.790 --> 00:06:53.520
Bilbo Baggins of the Shire.

73
00:06:53.727 --> 00:06:55.490
A ring.

74
00:06:55.695 --> 00:06:57.560
Lost!

75
00:07:00.333 --> 00:07:03.769
My precious is lost!

76
00:07:04.003 --> 00:07:06.301
For the time will soon come...

77
00:07:06.539 --> 00:07:11.704
...when Hobbits will shape
the fortunes of all.

78
00:07:27.293 --> 00:07:31.787
The Shire... 60 years later

79
00:07:34.200 --> 00:07:37.727
Down from the door where it began

80
00:07:42.575 --> 00:07:46.375
And I must follow if I can

81
00:07:47.380 --> 00:07:51.510
The road goes ever on and on

82
00:07:51.718 --> 00:07:55.176
Down from the door where it began

83
00:07:55.388 --> 00:08:00.348
Now far ahead the road has gone

84
00:08:01.027 --> 00:08:04.758
- And I must follow if I can
- You're late.

85
00:08:08.067 --> 00:08:11.867
A wizard is never late. Frodo Baggins.

86
00:08:12.639 --> 00:08:17.269
Nor is he early. He arrives
precisely when he means to.

87
00:08:28.621 --> 00:08:31.681
It's wonderful to see you. Gandalf!

88
00:08:35.595 --> 00:08:39.292
You didn't think I'd miss
your Uncle Bilbo's birthday?

89
00:08:40.934 --> 00:08:43.596
What news of the outside world?
Tell me everything.

90
00:08:43.837 --> 00:08:47.603
Everything? You're far too eager
and curious for a Hobbit.

91
00:08:48.074 --> 00:08:49.200
Most unnatural.

92
00:08:51.744 --> 00:08:53.211
Well. what can I tell you?

93
00:08:53.413 --> 00:08:57.816
Life in the wide world goes on
much as it has this past Age.

94
00:08:58.017 --> 00:09:00.645
Full of its own comings and goings.

95
00:09:00.854 --> 00:09:03.721
Scarcely aware of the existence
of Hobbits.

96
00:09:04.457 --> 00:09:06.982
For which I am very thankful.

97
00:09:11.564 --> 00:09:13.964
It's Gandalf!

98
00:09:25.945 --> 00:09:29.176
The long-expected party.

99
00:09:35.288 --> 00:09:36.983
How is the old rascal?

100
00:09:37.190 --> 00:09:40.591
I hear it's going to be a party
of special magnificence.

101
00:09:40.760 --> 00:09:43.786
You know Bilbo.
He's got the whole place in an uproar.

102
00:09:43.963 --> 00:09:45.692
Well. that should please him.

103
00:09:45.899 --> 00:09:48.265
- Half the Shire's been invited.
- Gracious me.

104
00:09:48.468 --> 00:09:50.299
- He's up to something.
- Oh. really?

105
00:09:50.470 --> 00:09:52.529
All right. then. Keep your secrets.

106
00:09:52.772 --> 00:09:55.172
Before you came along. we Bagginses
were very well thought of.

107
00:09:55.341 --> 00:09:56.137
Indeed.

108
00:09:56.309 --> 00:09:58.539
Never had any adventures
or did anything unexpected.

109
00:09:59.145 --> 00:10:05.015
If you're referring to the incident
with the dragon. I was barely involved.

110
00:10:05.218 --> 00:10:08.779
All I did was give your uncle
a little nudge out of the door.

111
00:10:08.988 --> 00:10:13.084
Whatever you did. you've been officially
labeled a disturber of the peace.

112
00:10:13.459 --> 00:10:15.359
Oh. really?

113
00:10:21.034 --> 00:10:22.934
Gandalf! Gandalf!

114
00:10:29.108 --> 00:10:30.302
Fireworks. Gandalf!

115
00:10:33.413 --> 00:10:36.041
- Gandalf!
- Fireworks. Gandalf!

116
00:10:54.634 --> 00:10:55.692
Gandalf?

117
00:10:56.269 --> 00:11:00.330
- I'm glad you're back.
- So am l. dear boy.

118
00:11:04.444 --> 00:11:06.275
So am I.

119
00:11:38.111 --> 00:11:39.544
No. thank you!

120
00:11:39.746 --> 00:11:43.682
We don't want any more visitors.
well-wishers or distant relations!

121
00:11:43.883 --> 00:11:47.410
And what about very old friends?

122
00:11:50.556 --> 00:11:52.285
Gandalf?

123
00:11:52.892 --> 00:11:56.419
- Bilbo Baggins.
- My dear Gandalf!

124
00:11:56.629 --> 00:12:01.726
Good to see you. 111 years old!
Who would believe it?

125
00:12:03.503 --> 00:12:05.494
You haven't aged a day.

126
00:12:12.178 --> 00:12:14.146
Come on. come in!

127
00:12:14.347 --> 00:12:16.713
Welcome. welcome.

128
00:12:17.884 --> 00:12:20.444
Oh. here we are.

129
00:12:22.121 --> 00:12:24.555
Tea? Or maybe something
a little stronger?

130
00:12:24.724 --> 00:12:28.524
I've got a few bottles
of the Old Winyard left. 1 296.

131
00:12:28.728 --> 00:12:32.789
Very good year. Almost as old as I am.

132
00:12:33.966 --> 00:12:38.426
It was laid down by my father.
What say we open one. eh?

133
00:12:38.638 --> 00:12:41.266
Just tea. thank you.

134
00:12:47.713 --> 00:12:49.340
I was expecting you sometime
last week.

135
00:12:49.549 --> 00:12:52.848
Not that it matters. You come and go as
you please. Always have and always will.

136
00:12:53.052 --> 00:12:58.285
You caught me a bit unprepared. We've only
got cold chicken and a bit of pickle...

137
00:12:58.491 --> 00:13:01.858
There's some cheese here.
No. that won't do.

138
00:13:02.061 --> 00:13:05.963
We've got raspberry jam.
an apple tart...

139
00:13:06.666 --> 00:13:10.659
But not much for afters.
Oh. no. we're all right.

140
00:13:10.870 --> 00:13:13.703
I've just found some sponge cake.

141
00:13:16.576 --> 00:13:17.907
I could make you some eggs
if you'd...

142
00:13:21.747 --> 00:13:24.409
- Just tea. thank you.
- Oh. right.

143
00:13:25.518 --> 00:13:27.816
- You don't mind if I eat. do you?
- No. not at all.

144
00:13:28.921 --> 00:13:30.786
Bilbo! Bilbo Baggins!

145
00:13:30.990 --> 00:13:32.582
I'm not at home!

146
00:13:33.092 --> 00:13:36.323
I've got to get away from these confounded
relatives. hanging on the bell all day...

147
00:13:36.529 --> 00:13:38.463
...never giving me a moment's peace.

148
00:13:38.664 --> 00:13:42.225
I want to see mountains again.
Mountains. Gandalf!

149
00:13:42.401 --> 00:13:46.963
And then find somewhere quiet
where I can finish my book. Oh. tea.

150
00:13:47.140 --> 00:13:51.099
- So you mean to go through with your plan?
- Yes. yes. It's all in hand.

151
00:13:51.277 --> 00:13:53.541
All the arrangements are made.

152
00:13:55.314 --> 00:13:57.214
Oh. thank you.

153
00:13:57.383 --> 00:13:59.749
Frodo suspects something.

154
00:13:59.919 --> 00:14:02.387
Of course he does. He's a Baggins...

155
00:14:02.588 --> 00:14:05.216
...not some blockheaded Bracegirdle
from Hard bottle.

156
00:14:05.691 --> 00:14:08.558
You will tell him. won't you?

157
00:14:09.428 --> 00:14:11.453
- Yes. yes.
- He's very fond of you.

158
00:14:13.666 --> 00:14:15.224
I know.

159
00:14:17.503 --> 00:14:20.939
He'd probably come with me
if I asked him.

160
00:14:21.541 --> 00:14:24.977
I think in his heart. Frodo's
still in love with the Shire.

161
00:14:26.512 --> 00:14:28.878
The woods. the fields.

162
00:14:29.081 --> 00:14:31.413
Little rivers.

163
00:14:35.855 --> 00:14:38.551
I am old. Gandalf.

164
00:14:39.926 --> 00:14:45.193
I know I don't look it. but I'm
beginning to feel it in my heart.

165
00:14:47.366 --> 00:14:49.891
I feel thin.

166
00:14:50.102 --> 00:14:51.797
Sort of stretched...

167
00:14:53.105 --> 00:14:56.404
...like butter scraped
over too much bread.

168
00:14:56.609 --> 00:15:01.103
I need a holiday. A very long holiday.

169
00:15:01.314 --> 00:15:04.511
And I don't expect I shall return.

170
00:15:06.719 --> 00:15:09.916
In fact. I mean not to.

171
00:15:12.625 --> 00:15:16.686
Old Toby. The finest weed
in the South farthing.

172
00:15:34.046 --> 00:15:36.640
Gandalf. my old friend...

173
00:15:36.816 --> 00:15:39.649
...this will be a night to remember.

174
00:16:02.441 --> 00:16:03.533
Hello. hello.

175
00:16:03.776 --> 00:16:07.837
Fatty Bolger. Lovely to see you.
Welcome. welcome.

176
00:16:08.881 --> 00:16:11.406
Go on. Sam. Ask Rosie for a dance.

177
00:16:14.053 --> 00:16:17.580
- I think I'll just have another ale.
- Oh. no. you don't.

178
00:16:18.624 --> 00:16:20.421
Go on!

179
00:16:30.569 --> 00:16:32.400
So there I was...

180
00:16:32.605 --> 00:16:36.666
...at the mercy
of three monstrous trolls.

181
00:16:36.876 --> 00:16:38.867
And they were all arguing
amongst themselves...

182
00:16:39.078 --> 00:16:41.444
...about how they were
going to cook us.

183
00:16:41.647 --> 00:16:46.675
Whether it be turned on a spit. or to sit
on us one by one. squash us into jelly.

184
00:16:47.720 --> 00:16:51.247
They spent so much time arguing
the whithertos and the whyfors...

185
00:16:51.457 --> 00:16:55.018
...that the sun's first light
crept over the top of the trees...

186
00:16:56.028 --> 00:16:58.553
...and turned them all to stone!

187
00:17:03.803 --> 00:17:05.236
Quickly.

188
00:17:09.375 --> 00:17:11.434
Up they go!

189
00:17:14.313 --> 00:17:15.507
No. the big one.

190
00:17:25.658 --> 00:17:27.717
- Done!
- You're supposed to stick it in the ground.

191
00:17:27.927 --> 00:17:29.394
- It is in the ground.
- Outside!

192
00:17:29.562 --> 00:17:31.223
This was your idea.

193
00:17:50.816 --> 00:17:52.443
Watch out for the dragon!

194
00:17:52.651 --> 00:17:56.018
Nonsense. There hasn't been a dragon
in these parts for a thousand years.

195
00:18:09.502 --> 00:18:13.097
- That was good.
- Let's get another one.

196
00:18:14.407 --> 00:18:18.935
Meriadoc Brandybuck and Peregrin Took.

197
00:18:19.145 --> 00:18:21.010
I might've known.

198
00:18:26.886 --> 00:18:28.945
Speech. Bilbo!

199
00:18:29.855 --> 00:18:31.186
Speech!

200
00:18:31.357 --> 00:18:32.346
Speech!

201
00:18:37.730 --> 00:18:39.960
My dear Bagginses and Boffins...

202
00:18:40.766 --> 00:18:42.961
...Tooks and Brandybucks...

203
00:18:43.169 --> 00:18:45.660
...Grubbs. Chubbs...

204
00:18:45.871 --> 00:18:46.895
...Horn blowers...

205
00:18:48.073 --> 00:18:49.734
...Bolgers...

206
00:18:50.109 --> 00:18:51.667
...Brace girdles...

207
00:18:51.877 --> 00:18:54.471
...and Proud foots.
- Proud feet!

208
00:18:56.682 --> 00:18:59.810
Today is my 111th birthday!

209
00:19:01.620 --> 00:19:03.178
Happy birthday!

210
00:19:03.389 --> 00:19:07.655
But alas. eleventy-one years is
far too short a time to live among...

211
00:19:07.860 --> 00:19:10.761
...such excellent
and admirable Hobbits.

212
00:19:11.697 --> 00:19:14.427
I don't know half of you
half as well as I should like...

213
00:19:14.633 --> 00:19:19.229
...and I like less than half of you
half as well as you deserve.

214
00:19:29.181 --> 00:19:31.581
I have things to do.

215
00:19:37.957 --> 00:19:40.084
I've put this off far too long.

216
00:19:43.929 --> 00:19:47.865
I regret to announce this is the end!

217
00:19:49.034 --> 00:19:50.194
I'm going now.

218
00:19:51.337 --> 00:19:54.204
I bid you all a very fond farewell.

219
00:19:56.609 --> 00:19:57.803
Goodbye.

220
00:20:31.043 --> 00:20:34.171
I suppose you think
that was terribly clever.

221
00:20:34.380 --> 00:20:37.747
Come on. Gandalf.
Did you see their faces?

222
00:20:37.950 --> 00:20:42.978
There are many magic rings in this world.
and none of them should be used lightly.

223
00:20:43.188 --> 00:20:45.349
It was just a bit of fun.

224
00:20:45.558 --> 00:20:49.255
Oh. you're probably right. as usual.

225
00:20:50.663 --> 00:20:54.190
- You will keep an eye on Frodo. won't you?
- Two eyes.

226
00:20:54.400 --> 00:20:57.062
As often as I can spare them.

227
00:20:57.269 --> 00:21:00.466
- I'm leaving everything to him.
- What about this ring of yours?

228
00:21:00.673 --> 00:21:04.006
- Is that staying too?
- Yes. yes.

229
00:21:04.643 --> 00:21:08.511
It's in an envelope over there
on the mantelpiece.

230
00:21:09.582 --> 00:21:12.551
No. Wait. it's...

231
00:21:15.054 --> 00:21:17.750
...here in my pocket.

232
00:21:22.227 --> 00:21:25.594
Isn't that...? Isn't that odd. now?

233
00:21:27.266 --> 00:21:30.758
Yet. after all. why not?

234
00:21:32.338 --> 00:21:37.207
- Why shouldn't I keep it?
- I think you should leave the ring behind.

235
00:21:37.610 --> 00:21:39.805
Is that so hard?

236
00:21:40.012 --> 00:21:41.343
Well. no.

237
00:21:43.716 --> 00:21:45.240
And yes.

238
00:21:47.219 --> 00:21:50.279
Now it comes to it.
I don't feel like parting with it.

239
00:21:50.489 --> 00:21:52.252
It's mine. I found it! It came to me!

240
00:21:52.458 --> 00:21:56.656
- There's no need to get angry.
- Well. if I'm angry. it's your fault!

241
00:21:57.129 --> 00:21:58.926
It's mine.

242
00:22:00.199 --> 00:22:02.667
My own.

243
00:22:03.002 --> 00:22:06.995
- My precious.
- Precious?

244
00:22:07.206 --> 00:22:10.073
It's been called that before.
but not by you.

245
00:22:10.309 --> 00:22:12.869
What business is it of yours
what I do with my own things?

246
00:22:13.078 --> 00:22:15.808
I think you've had that ring
quite long enough.

247
00:22:16.015 --> 00:22:18.882
- You want it for yourself!
- Bilbo Baggins!

248
00:22:19.084 --> 00:22:23.316
Do not take me for some conjurer
of cheap tricks.

249
00:22:23.522 --> 00:22:27.185
I am not trying to rob you.

250
00:22:32.231 --> 00:22:33.926
I'm trying to help you.

251
00:22:42.374 --> 00:22:45.741
All your long years.
we've been friends.

252
00:22:46.145 --> 00:22:48.272
Trust me as you once did.

253
00:22:50.149 --> 00:22:51.980
Let it go.

254
00:22:53.052 --> 00:22:55.520
You're right. Gandalf.

255
00:22:57.623 --> 00:23:00.319
The ring must go to Frodo.

256
00:23:01.660 --> 00:23:04.629
It's late. The road is long.

257
00:23:04.830 --> 00:23:07.321
Yes. it is time.

258
00:23:12.638 --> 00:23:15.129
The ring is still in your pocket.

259
00:23:49.842 --> 00:23:52.868
I've thought up an ending for my book:

260
00:23:54.513 --> 00:23:59.541
"And he lived happily ever after
to the end of his days."

261
00:23:59.718 --> 00:24:03.154
And I'm sure you will. my dear friend.

262
00:24:04.189 --> 00:24:05.622
Goodbye. Gandalf.

263
00:24:08.127 --> 00:24:11.028
Goodbye. dear Bilbo.

264
00:24:18.837 --> 00:24:23.069
The road goes ever on and on

265
00:24:25.611 --> 00:24:28.045
Until our next meeting.

266
00:24:55.340 --> 00:24:59.003
It's mine. My own.

267
00:24:59.178 --> 00:25:02.636
My precious.

268
00:25:02.915 --> 00:25:05.816
Riddles in the dark.

269
00:25:06.051 --> 00:25:07.484
Bilbo!

270
00:25:07.653 --> 00:25:09.211
Bilbo!

271
00:25:12.825 --> 00:25:15.794
My precious.

272
00:25:17.396 --> 00:25:19.626
Precious.

273
00:25:19.798 --> 00:25:22.323
He's gone. hasn't he?

274
00:25:25.103 --> 00:25:28.163
He talked for so long about leaving...

275
00:25:28.373 --> 00:25:31.103
...I didn't think he'd really do it.

276
00:25:35.581 --> 00:25:37.481
Gandalf?

277
00:25:45.724 --> 00:25:47.419
Bilbo's ring.

278
00:25:47.759 --> 00:25:50.125
He's gone to stay with the Elves.

279
00:25:50.329 --> 00:25:53.423
He's left you Bag End.

280
00:25:57.035 --> 00:25:59.560
Along with all his possessions.

281
00:25:59.771 --> 00:26:02.672
The ring is yours now.

282
00:26:05.244 --> 00:26:08.771
- Put it somewhere out of sight.
- Where are you going?

283
00:26:08.947 --> 00:26:11.211
- There are some things that I must see to.
- What things?

284
00:26:11.383 --> 00:26:15.683
- Questions. Questions that need answering.
- You've only just arrived.

285
00:26:16.555 --> 00:26:19.183
I don't understand.

286
00:26:22.494 --> 00:26:23.518
Neither do I.

287
00:26:26.765 --> 00:26:29.097
Keep it secret.

288
00:26:29.268 --> 00:26:31.065
Keep it safe.

289
00:27:06.071 --> 00:27:08.232
Shire!

290
00:27:08.540 --> 00:27:11.634
Baggins!

291
00:28:00.192 --> 00:28:03.127
"The year 3434 of the Second Age.

292
00:28:03.328 --> 00:28:07.731
Here follows the account of Isildur.
High King of Gondor...

293
00:28:07.933 --> 00:28:11.596
...and the finding
of the Ring of Power. "

294
00:28:15.107 --> 00:28:16.938
"It has come to me.

295
00:28:17.142 --> 00:28:20.600
The One Ring. It shall be
an heirloom of my kingdom.

296
00:28:20.812 --> 00:28:24.248
All those who follow in my bloodline
shall be bound to its fate...

297
00:28:24.449 --> 00:28:28.249
...for I will risk
no hurt to the Ring.

298
00:28:28.453 --> 00:28:30.944
It is precious to me...

299
00:28:31.823 --> 00:28:34.451
...though I buy it with great pain.

300
00:28:37.596 --> 00:28:41.794
The markings upon the band
begin to fade.

301
00:28:42.134 --> 00:28:46.833
The writing. which at first was as clear
as red flame. has all but disappeared.

302
00:28:47.039 --> 00:28:51.100
A secret now
that only fire can tell. "

303
00:29:07.626 --> 00:29:10.595
Shire.

304
00:29:10.796 --> 00:29:12.764
Baggins.

305
00:29:13.265 --> 00:29:17.326
There's no Bagginses around here.
They're all up in Hobbiton.

306
00:29:19.037 --> 00:29:20.527
That way.

307
00:29:27.446 --> 00:29:29.937
- Good night.
- Good night.

308
00:29:31.550 --> 00:29:33.040
Good night. Sam.

309
00:29:59.177 --> 00:30:01.645
Is it secret? Is it safe?

310
00:30:10.555 --> 00:30:12.682
What are you doing?

311
00:30:25.270 --> 00:30:27.830
Hold out your hand. Frodo.

312
00:30:28.039 --> 00:30:29.199
It's quite cool.

313
00:30:32.711 --> 00:30:34.474
What can you see?

314
00:30:36.248 --> 00:30:38.648
Can you see anything?

315
00:30:41.386 --> 00:30:42.751
Nothing.

316
00:30:43.421 --> 00:30:45.412
There's nothing.

317
00:30:46.491 --> 00:30:47.981
Wait.

318
00:30:52.097 --> 00:30:54.327
There are markings.

319
00:30:55.767 --> 00:30:59.225
It's some form of Elvish.
I can't read it.

320
00:30:59.437 --> 00:31:01.997
There are few who can.

321
00:31:02.574 --> 00:31:07.409
The language is that of Mordor.
which I will not utter here.

322
00:31:08.079 --> 00:31:09.068
Mordor!

323
00:31:09.347 --> 00:31:11.338
In the common tongue. it says:

324
00:31:11.550 --> 00:31:15.077
"One Ring to rule them all...

325
00:31:15.287 --> 00:31:17.619
...One Ring to find them...

326
00:31:17.822 --> 00:31:20.017
...One Ring to bring them all...

327
00:31:20.292 --> 00:31:23.318
...and in the darkness bind them."

328
00:31:24.963 --> 00:31:26.988
This is the One Ring...

329
00:31:27.199 --> 00:31:32.466
...forged by the Dark Lord Sauron
in the fires of Mount Doom.

330
00:31:32.671 --> 00:31:36.698
Taken by Isildur
from the hand of Sauron himself.

331
00:31:37.475 --> 00:31:40.035
Bilbo found it.

332
00:31:40.478 --> 00:31:42.446
- In Gollum's cave.
- Yes.

333
00:31:42.647 --> 00:31:47.175
For 60 years. the Ring lay quiet
in Bilbo's keeping...

334
00:31:47.385 --> 00:31:50.752
...prolonging his life.
delaying old age.

335
00:31:51.456 --> 00:31:55.825
But no longer. Frodo.
Evil is stirring in Mordor.

336
00:31:56.027 --> 00:31:58.461
The Ring has awoken.

337
00:31:58.663 --> 00:32:01.393
It's heard its master's call.

338
00:32:01.633 --> 00:32:05.501
But he was destroyed.
Sauron was destroyed.

339
00:32:11.209 --> 00:32:13.302
No. Frodo.

340
00:32:14.246 --> 00:32:17.545
The spirit of Sauron endured.

341
00:32:17.749 --> 00:32:23.085
His life force is bound to the Ring.
and the Ring survived.

342
00:32:23.355 --> 00:32:25.550
Sauron has returned.

343
00:32:26.458 --> 00:32:28.551
His Orcs have multiplied.

344
00:32:28.760 --> 00:32:32.787
His fortress at Barad-d�r
is rebuilt in the land of Mordor.

345
00:32:32.998 --> 00:32:37.765
Sauron needs only this Ring to cover
all the lands in a second darkness.

346
00:32:37.969 --> 00:32:40.028
He is seeking it.

347
00:32:40.238 --> 00:32:44.106
Seeking it. All his thought
is bent on it.

348
00:32:44.309 --> 00:32:47.039
For the Ring yearns above all else...

349
00:32:47.245 --> 00:32:50.681
...to return to the hand
of its master.

350
00:32:50.882 --> 00:32:52.645
They are one...

351
00:32:52.851 --> 00:32:55.979
...the Ring and the Dark Lord.

352
00:32:56.187 --> 00:32:57.176
Frodo...

353
00:32:57.722 --> 00:32:59.656
...he must never find it.

354
00:32:59.858 --> 00:33:00.847
All right.

355
00:33:01.192 --> 00:33:05.492
We put it away. We keep it hidden.
We never speak of it again.

356
00:33:05.697 --> 00:33:08.325
No one knows it's here. do they?

357
00:33:14.039 --> 00:33:15.233
Do they. Gandalf?

358
00:33:16.274 --> 00:33:19.710
There is one other who knew
that Bilbo had the Ring.

359
00:33:20.912 --> 00:33:23.938
I looked everywhere
for the creature Gollum.

360
00:33:24.149 --> 00:33:26.276
But the enemy found him first.

361
00:33:28.019 --> 00:33:30.510
I don't know how long
they tortured him.

362
00:33:30.689 --> 00:33:35.183
But amidst the endless screams and
inane babble. they discerned two words:

363
00:33:35.393 --> 00:33:37.520
Shire!

364
00:33:37.729 --> 00:33:39.321
Baggins!

365
00:33:39.531 --> 00:33:41.362
Shire.

366
00:33:41.566 --> 00:33:44.433
Baggins. But that would
lead them here!

367
00:33:47.172 --> 00:33:48.298
Who goes there?

368
00:33:50.075 --> 00:33:51.269
Take it. Gandalf!

369
00:33:51.676 --> 00:33:52.700
- Take it!
- No. Frodo.

370
00:33:52.911 --> 00:33:55.277
- You must take it!
- You cannot offer me this ring!

371
00:33:55.480 --> 00:33:58.813
- I'm giving it to you!
- Don't tempt me. Frodo!

372
00:34:00.352 --> 00:34:02.582
I dare not take it.

373
00:34:02.887 --> 00:34:05.355
Not even to keep it safe.

374
00:34:06.458 --> 00:34:08.483
Understand. Frodo...

375
00:34:09.160 --> 00:34:12.789
...I would use this Ring
from a desire to do good.

376
00:34:18.203 --> 00:34:23.903
But through me. it would wield a power
too great and terrible to imagine.

377
00:34:24.509 --> 00:34:27.444
- But it cannot stay in the Shire!
- No.

378
00:34:29.314 --> 00:34:30.906
No. it can't.

379
00:34:36.287 --> 00:34:37.652
What must I do?

380
00:34:39.324 --> 00:34:42.851
- You must leave. And leave quickly.
- Where? Where do I go?

381
00:34:43.061 --> 00:34:46.326
Get out of the Shire.
Make for the village of Bree.

382
00:34:46.598 --> 00:34:47.690
Bree.

383
00:34:47.899 --> 00:34:50.663
- What about you?
- I'll be waiting for you...

384
00:34:50.869 --> 00:34:53.337
...at the inn of the Prancing Pony.

385
00:34:53.538 --> 00:34:57.269
- And the Ring will be safe there?
- I don't know. Frodo.

386
00:34:57.475 --> 00:34:59.443
I don't have any answers.

387
00:35:00.979 --> 00:35:06.508
I must see the head of my order. He is
both wise and powerful. Trust me. Frodo.

388
00:35:06.718 --> 00:35:08.845
He'll know what to do.

389
00:35:09.454 --> 00:35:12.321
You'll have to leave the name
of Baggins behind you.

390
00:35:12.524 --> 00:35:15.015
That name is not safe
outside the Shire.

391
00:35:15.693 --> 00:35:18.992
Travel only by day.
And stay off the road.

392
00:35:19.631 --> 00:35:22.828
I can cut across country
easily enough.

393
00:35:25.336 --> 00:35:26.667
My dear Frodo.

394
00:35:26.938 --> 00:35:29.998
Hobbits really are amazing creatures.

395
00:35:30.175 --> 00:35:33.076
You can learn all that there is to
know about their ways in a month.

396
00:35:33.278 --> 00:35:35.644
And yet. after a hundred years...

397
00:35:35.847 --> 00:35:37.872
...they can still surprise you.

398
00:35:39.484 --> 00:35:40.815
Get down.

399
00:35:53.064 --> 00:35:56.556
Confound it all. Samwise Gamgee!
Have you been eavesdropping?

400
00:35:56.734 --> 00:36:01.228
I haven't been dropping no eaves. Honest.
I was cutting the grass under the window.

401
00:36:01.406 --> 00:36:03.874
A little late for trimming the verge.
don't you think?

402
00:36:04.042 --> 00:36:06.909
- I heard raised voices.
- What did you hear? Speak!

403
00:36:07.078 --> 00:36:08.204
Nothing important.

404
00:36:08.746 --> 00:36:12.842
That is. I heard a good deal about a ring.
a Dark Lord and the end of the world but...

405
00:36:13.017 --> 00:36:17.784
Please. Mr. Gandalf. sir. don't hurt me.
Don't turn me into anything unnatural.

406
00:36:18.490 --> 00:36:20.117
No?

407
00:36:21.326 --> 00:36:22.452
Perhaps not.

408
00:36:23.728 --> 00:36:27.129
I've thought of a better use for you.

409
00:36:28.900 --> 00:36:31.892
Come along. Samwise. Keep up.

410
00:36:33.371 --> 00:36:35.601
Be careful. both of you.

411
00:36:35.874 --> 00:36:38.638
The enemy has many spies
in his service:

412
00:36:38.910 --> 00:36:41.811
Birds. beasts.

413
00:36:43.581 --> 00:36:45.412
Is it safe?

414
00:36:47.085 --> 00:36:48.450
Never put it on...

415
00:36:48.653 --> 00:36:52.054
...for the agents of the Dark Lord
will be drawn to its power.

416
00:36:52.257 --> 00:36:53.747
Always remember. Frodo...

417
00:36:54.259 --> 00:36:57.422
...the Ring is trying to get back
to its master.

418
00:36:57.795 --> 00:36:59.922
It wants to be found.

419
00:37:40.505 --> 00:37:42.700
This is it.

420
00:37:43.041 --> 00:37:45.168
This is what?

421
00:37:45.510 --> 00:37:47.569
If I take one more step...

422
00:37:48.079 --> 00:37:51.947
...it'll be the farthest away
from home I've ever been.

423
00:37:56.187 --> 00:37:57.677
Come on. Sam.

424
00:38:06.130 --> 00:38:07.995
Remember what Bilbo used to say:

425
00:38:08.533 --> 00:38:12.333
- "It's a dangerous business. Frodo."
- "Going out your door.

426
00:38:12.503 --> 00:38:16.940
You step onto the road.
and if you don't keep your feet...

427
00:38:17.108 --> 00:38:21.272
...there's no knowing where
you might be swept off to. "

428
00:38:45.570 --> 00:38:48.630
Smoke rises
from the Mountain of Doom.

429
00:38:48.806 --> 00:38:50.467
The hour grows late.

430
00:38:50.642 --> 00:38:54.237
And Gandalf the Grey
rides to Isengard...

431
00:38:54.445 --> 00:38:56.879
...seeking my counsel.

432
00:38:57.081 --> 00:39:01.074
For that is why you have come.
is it not?

433
00:39:01.252 --> 00:39:02.549
My old friend.

434
00:39:02.820 --> 00:39:04.412
Saruman.

435
00:39:09.193 --> 00:39:12.219
- You are sure of this?
- Beyond any doubt.

436
00:39:13.031 --> 00:39:15.329
So the Ring of Power has been found.

437
00:39:15.500 --> 00:39:18.697
All these long years.
it was in the Shire.

438
00:39:18.936 --> 00:39:22.133
- Under my very nose.
- Yet you did not have the wit to see it.

439
00:39:22.707 --> 00:39:27.144
Your love of the halfling's leaf
has clearly slowed your mind.

440
00:39:27.845 --> 00:39:32.043
But we still have time. Time enough
to counter Sauron if we act quickly.

441
00:39:32.250 --> 00:39:33.717
Time?

442
00:39:34.686 --> 00:39:37.314
What time do you think we have?

443
00:39:37.755 --> 00:39:41.623
Sauron has regained
much of his former strength.

444
00:39:41.793 --> 00:39:44.023
He cannot yet take physical form...

445
00:39:44.195 --> 00:39:46.925
...but his spirit has lost
none of its potency.

446
00:39:47.598 --> 00:39:52.661
Concealed within his fortress.
the Lord of Mordor sees all.

447
00:39:53.204 --> 00:39:59.165
His gaze pierces cloud. shadow.
earth and flesh.

448
00:40:00.678 --> 00:40:03.806
You know of what I speak. Gandalf.

449
00:40:04.716 --> 00:40:09.983
A Great Eye. lidless.
wreathed in flame.

450
00:40:10.955 --> 00:40:12.718
The Eye of Sauron.

451
00:40:12.957 --> 00:40:15.517
He is gathering all evil to him.

452
00:40:15.727 --> 00:40:20.596
Very soon. he'll have summoned an army
great enough for an assault upon Middle-earth.

453
00:40:20.932 --> 00:40:23.332
You know this?

454
00:40:23.868 --> 00:40:25.358
How?

455
00:40:25.937 --> 00:40:27.598
I have seen it.

456
00:40:28.039 --> 00:40:31.236
A palant�r is a dangerous tool.
Saruman.

457
00:40:31.943 --> 00:40:33.433
Why?

458
00:40:33.911 --> 00:40:36.641
Why should we fear to use it?

459
00:40:39.250 --> 00:40:43.243
They are not all accounted for.
the lost Seeing-stones.

460
00:40:43.421 --> 00:40:46.618
We do not know who else
may be watching.

461
00:40:49.227 --> 00:40:51.957
The hour is later than you think.

462
00:40:52.130 --> 00:40:54.496
Sauron's forces are already moving.

463
00:40:56.734 --> 00:40:59.498
The Nine have left Minas Morgul.

464
00:40:59.904 --> 00:41:00.893
The Nine?

465
00:41:01.072 --> 00:41:04.132
They crossed the River Isen
on Midsummer's Eve...

466
00:41:04.308 --> 00:41:07.004
...disguised as riders in black.

467
00:41:07.211 --> 00:41:11.170
- They've reached the Shire?
- They will find the Ring.

468
00:41:12.784 --> 00:41:14.979
And kill the one who carries it.

469
00:41:15.520 --> 00:41:17.010
Frodo!

470
00:41:29.600 --> 00:41:34.003
You did not seriously think that a Hobbit
could contend with the will of Sauron?

471
00:41:34.772 --> 00:41:37.570
There are none who can.

472
00:41:40.077 --> 00:41:42.807
Against the power of Mordor...

473
00:41:42.980 --> 00:41:45.608
...there can be no victory.

474
00:41:47.585 --> 00:41:50.748
We must join with him. Gandalf.

475
00:41:52.023 --> 00:41:54.389
We must join with Sauron.

476
00:41:57.028 --> 00:41:59.690
It would be wise. my friend.

477
00:42:00.164 --> 00:42:01.688
Tell me...

478
00:42:01.866 --> 00:42:02.855
...friend...

479
00:42:03.868 --> 00:42:08.430
...when did Saruman the Wise
abandon reason for madness?

480
00:42:47.945 --> 00:42:49.640
I gave you the chance...

481
00:42:50.748 --> 00:42:53.444
...of aiding me willingly...

482
00:42:53.618 --> 00:42:57.782
...but you have elected
the way of pain!

483
00:43:21.078 --> 00:43:22.568
Mr. Frodo?

484
00:43:23.180 --> 00:43:24.977
Frodo? Frodo!

485
00:43:26.384 --> 00:43:29.615
- I thought I'd lost you.
- What are you talking about?

486
00:43:29.787 --> 00:43:32.813
- It's just something Gandalf said.
- What did he say?

487
00:43:33.624 --> 00:43:37.526
"Don't you lose him. Samwise Gamgee."
And I don't mean to.

488
00:43:37.762 --> 00:43:41.391
Sam. we're still in the Shire.
What could possibly happen?

489
00:43:44.402 --> 00:43:45.391
Frodo.

490
00:43:45.636 --> 00:43:47.900
- Merry. it's Frodo Baggins.
- Hello. Frodo.

491
00:43:48.105 --> 00:43:49.504
Get off him.

492
00:43:50.007 --> 00:43:51.474
Come on. Frodo.

493
00:43:51.676 --> 00:43:53.541
What's the meaning of this?

494
00:43:53.978 --> 00:43:57.072
You've been into Farmer Maggot's crop!

495
00:43:58.249 --> 00:44:00.376
You get back here!

496
00:44:01.385 --> 00:44:02.716
Get out of my field!

497
00:44:02.887 --> 00:44:05.720
You know what's gonna happen
when I catch up with you?

498
00:44:05.923 --> 00:44:08.892
I don't know why he's so upset.
It's only a couple of carrots.

499
00:44:09.060 --> 00:44:10.186
And some cabbages.

500
00:44:10.361 --> 00:44:13.296
And those three bags of potatoes
that we lifted last week.

501
00:44:13.464 --> 00:44:17.525
- And then the mushrooms the week before.
- Yes. Pippin. My point is...

502
00:44:17.735 --> 00:44:19.896
...he's clearly overreacting.

503
00:44:20.104 --> 00:44:21.594
Run!

504
00:44:35.086 --> 00:44:37.611
Oh. that was close.

505
00:44:38.689 --> 00:44:41.817
I think I've broken something.

506
00:44:42.827 --> 00:44:45.193
Trust a Brandybuck and a Took!

507
00:44:45.363 --> 00:44:49.026
What? That was just a detour.
A shortcut.

508
00:44:49.200 --> 00:44:51.464
- Shortcut to what?
- Mushrooms!

509
00:45:00.244 --> 00:45:01.734
That's mine.

510
00:45:04.482 --> 00:45:06.109
That's nice. Merry.

511
00:45:06.650 --> 00:45:08.675
Here's a nice one. Sam.

512
00:45:08.853 --> 00:45:11.413
I think we should get off the road.

513
00:45:20.598 --> 00:45:21.963
Get off the road!

514
00:45:22.166 --> 00:45:23.656
Quick!

515
00:45:36.347 --> 00:45:37.837
Be quiet!

516
00:46:44.148 --> 00:46:46.309
What was that?

517
00:47:19.016 --> 00:47:20.506
Anything?

518
00:47:21.218 --> 00:47:22.708
Nothing.

519
00:47:23.420 --> 00:47:25.684
What is going on?

520
00:47:26.257 --> 00:47:30.057
That Black Rider was looking
for something. Or someone.

521
00:47:33.531 --> 00:47:34.520
Get down!

522
00:47:51.515 --> 00:47:53.710
I have to leave the Shire.

523
00:47:54.752 --> 00:47:57.084
Sam and I must get to Bree.

524
00:47:57.254 --> 00:47:58.687
Right.

525
00:48:00.090 --> 00:48:02.320
Bucklebury Ferry. Follow me.

526
00:48:10.634 --> 00:48:11.965
Run!

527
00:48:13.170 --> 00:48:15.161
This way! Follow me!

528
00:48:18.742 --> 00:48:19.800
Run!

529
00:48:33.123 --> 00:48:34.852
Get the rope. Sam!

530
00:48:37.494 --> 00:48:39.018
Frodo!

531
00:48:39.730 --> 00:48:41.163
Run. Frodo!

532
00:48:41.498 --> 00:48:42.590
Go!
- Hurry!

533
00:48:42.766 --> 00:48:45.394
Frodo. come on!

534
00:48:46.337 --> 00:48:48.362
- Come on! Faster!
- Jump!

535
00:49:03.287 --> 00:49:07.519
- How far to the nearest crossing?
- The Brandywine Bridge. 20 miles.

536
00:49:22.106 --> 00:49:23.596
Come on.

537
00:49:34.785 --> 00:49:38.243
- What do you want?
- We're heading for the Prancing Pony.

538
00:49:41.725 --> 00:49:44.592
Hobbits. Four Hobbits!

539
00:49:44.762 --> 00:49:48.163
- What business brings you to Bree?
- We wish to stay at the inn.

540
00:49:48.332 --> 00:49:50.391
Our business is our own.

541
00:49:50.567 --> 00:49:53.092
All right. young sir.
I meant no offense.

542
00:49:53.270 --> 00:49:55.795
It's my job to ask questions
after nightfall.

543
00:49:55.973 --> 00:49:58.840
There's talk of strange folk abroad.

544
00:49:59.009 --> 00:50:01.170
Can't be too careful.

545
00:50:20.898 --> 00:50:24.356
Out of the way!
Watch where you're walking.

546
00:50:48.392 --> 00:50:50.019
Excuse me.

547
00:50:51.095 --> 00:50:52.960
Good evening. little masters.

548
00:50:53.230 --> 00:50:57.997
If you're seeking accommodation. we got
some cozy Hobbit-sized rooms available.

549
00:50:58.168 --> 00:51:00.102
Mister...?

550
00:51:01.405 --> 00:51:03.464
Underhill. My name's Underhill.

551
00:51:04.708 --> 00:51:07.268
- Underhill. yes.
- We're friends of Gandalf the Grey.

552
00:51:07.444 --> 00:51:10.607
- Can you tell him we've arrived?
- Gandalf?

553
00:51:11.014 --> 00:51:12.777
Gandalf.

554
00:51:13.550 --> 00:51:15.279
Oh. yes...

555
00:51:15.486 --> 00:51:17.579
...I remember. Elderly chap.

556
00:51:17.888 --> 00:51:20.857
Big grey beard. pointy hat.

557
00:51:21.225 --> 00:51:23.056
Not seen him for six months.

558
00:51:29.867 --> 00:51:31.164
What do we do now?

559
00:51:38.375 --> 00:51:39.637
Sam...

560
00:51:39.810 --> 00:51:41.675
...he'll be here. He'll come.

561
00:51:44.415 --> 00:51:46.508
Get out of my way!

562
00:51:48.886 --> 00:51:50.547
What's that?

563
00:51:50.721 --> 00:51:53.246
This. my friend. is a pint.

564
00:51:53.424 --> 00:51:55.051
It comes in pints?

565
00:51:55.426 --> 00:51:59.123
- I'm getting one.
- You got a whole half already!

566
00:52:05.469 --> 00:52:09.337
That fellow's done nothing
but stare at you since we arrived.

567
00:52:12.876 --> 00:52:14.366
Excuse me.

568
00:52:16.180 --> 00:52:19.172
That Man in the corner. Who is he?

569
00:52:20.317 --> 00:52:24.720
He's one of them Rangers. They're
dangerous folk. wandering the Wilds.

570
00:52:25.022 --> 00:52:29.482
What his right name is. I've never heard.
but around here he's known as Strider.

571
00:52:31.895 --> 00:52:33.089
Strider.

572
00:52:46.143 --> 00:52:49.374
Baggins.

573
00:52:52.816 --> 00:52:54.340
Baggins.

574
00:53:06.697 --> 00:53:08.961
Baggins? Sure. I know a Baggins.

575
00:53:09.766 --> 00:53:12.633
He's over there. Frodo Baggins.

576
00:53:12.803 --> 00:53:15.897
He's my second cousin.
once removed on his mother's side...

577
00:53:16.073 --> 00:53:18.303
...and my third cousin. twice removed...

578
00:53:22.813 --> 00:53:24.610
- Pippin!
- Steady on. Frodo.

579
00:53:54.144 --> 00:53:56.612
You cannot hide.

580
00:53:59.550 --> 00:54:02.678
I see you.

581
00:54:04.388 --> 00:54:07.084
There is no life...

582
00:54:07.257 --> 00:54:09.487
...in the void.

583
00:54:09.660 --> 00:54:11.150
Only...

584
00:54:12.062 --> 00:54:13.552
...death.

585
00:54:19.570 --> 00:54:24.439
You draw far too much attention
to yourself. "Mr. Underhill."

586
00:54:29.112 --> 00:54:30.101
What do you want?

587
00:54:30.280 --> 00:54:32.373
A little more caution from you.
That is no trinket you carry.

588
00:54:32.783 --> 00:54:35.809
- I carry nothing.
- Indeed.

589
00:54:36.086 --> 00:54:38.611
I can avoid being seen if I wish...

590
00:54:38.789 --> 00:54:42.520
...but to disappear entirely.
that is a rare gift.

591
00:54:43.026 --> 00:54:45.620
- Who are you?
- Are you frightened?

592
00:54:46.897 --> 00:54:47.886
Yes.

593
00:54:48.065 --> 00:54:52.001
Not nearly frightened enough.
I know what hunts you.

594
00:54:55.973 --> 00:54:58.533
Let him go!
Or I'll have you. Longshanks.

595
00:55:00.210 --> 00:55:04.340
You have a stout heart. little Hobbit.
But that will not save you.

596
00:55:04.514 --> 00:55:07.449
You can no longer wait
for the wizard. Frodo.

597
00:55:07.618 --> 00:55:08.710
They're coming.

598
00:56:30.901 --> 00:56:32.391
What are they?

599
00:56:34.571 --> 00:56:36.698
They were once Men.

600
00:56:36.940 --> 00:56:39.135
Great kings of Men.

601
00:56:39.309 --> 00:56:42.472
Then Sauron the Deceiver gave to them
nine rings of power.

602
00:56:43.080 --> 00:56:46.208
Blinded by their greed.
they took them without question.

603
00:56:46.450 --> 00:56:49.749
One by one. falling into darkness.

604
00:56:49.920 --> 00:56:52.445
Now they are slaves to his will.

605
00:56:54.825 --> 00:56:56.520
They are the Nazg�l.

606
00:56:56.727 --> 00:56:59.457
Ring wraiths. Neither living nor dead.

607
00:57:00.197 --> 00:57:01.664
At all times they feel...

608
00:57:01.832 --> 00:57:03.800
...the presence of the Ring...

609
00:57:03.967 --> 00:57:08.495
...drawn to the power of the One.
They will never stop hunting you.

610
00:57:18.482 --> 00:57:21.417
- Where are you taking us?
- Into the Wild.

611
00:57:24.554 --> 00:57:28.615
How do we know this Strider
is a friend of Gandalf?

612
00:57:29.226 --> 00:57:32.093
We have no choice but to trust him.

613
00:57:32.262 --> 00:57:35.698
- But where is he leading us?
- To Rivendell. Master Gamgee.

614
00:57:35.866 --> 00:57:39.131
- To the house of Elrond.
- Did you hear that? Rivendell.

615
00:57:39.736 --> 00:57:42.500
We're going to see the Elves.

616
00:58:00.524 --> 00:58:04.756
- Gentlemen. we do not stop till nightfall.
- What about breakfast?

617
00:58:04.961 --> 00:58:07.657
- You've already had it.
- We've had one. yes.

618
00:58:07.864 --> 00:58:10.059
What about second breakfast?

619
00:58:13.470 --> 00:58:16.633
Don't think he knows
about second breakfast. Pip.

620
00:58:16.840 --> 00:58:22.073
What about elevenses? Luncheon?
Afternoon tea? Dinner? Supper?

621
00:58:22.279 --> 00:58:26.443
- He knows about them. doesn't he?
- I wouldn't count on it.

622
00:58:31.922 --> 00:58:33.514
Pippin!

623
00:58:36.827 --> 00:58:40.923
The power of Isengard
is at your command...

624
00:58:41.131 --> 00:58:45.568
...Sauron. Lord of the Earth.

625
00:58:48.905 --> 00:58:54.673
Build me an army worthy of Mordor.

626
00:59:00.283 --> 00:59:04.743
What orders from Mordor. my lord?
What does the Eye command?

627
00:59:05.188 --> 00:59:07.122
We have work to do.

628
00:59:49.766 --> 00:59:54.430
The trees are strong. my lord.
Their roots go deep.

629
00:59:54.804 --> 00:59:56.669
Rip them all down.

630
01:00:24.067 --> 01:00:27.002
This was the great watchtower
of Amon S�I.

631
01:00:28.705 --> 01:00:31.333
We shall rest here tonight.

632
01:00:42.986 --> 01:00:46.444
These are for you.
Keep them close.

633
01:00:46.656 --> 01:00:49.147
I'm going to have a look around.

634
01:00:51.528 --> 01:00:53.428
Stay here.

635
01:00:55.966 --> 01:00:58.161
My tomato's burst.

636
01:00:58.368 --> 01:01:00.268
Could I have some bacon?

637
01:01:00.470 --> 01:01:02.438
Want a tomato. Sam?

638
01:01:02.806 --> 01:01:06.503
- What are you doing?!
- Tomatoes. sausages. nice crispy bacon.

639
01:01:06.710 --> 01:01:09.372
- We saved some for you. Mr. Frodo.
- Put it out. you fools!

640
01:01:09.579 --> 01:01:13.572
- Put it out!
- That's nice! Ash on my tomatoes!

641
01:01:22.058 --> 01:01:23.753
Go!

642
01:02:17.247 --> 01:02:18.680
Back. you devils!

643
01:03:42.198 --> 01:03:43.392
Frodo!

644
01:03:48.138 --> 01:03:49.400
Oh. Sam.

645
01:04:26.376 --> 01:04:27.400
Strider!

646
01:04:30.146 --> 01:04:35.641
- Help him. Strider.
- He's been stabbed by a Morgul blade.

647
01:04:37.120 --> 01:04:42.080
This is beyond my skill to heal.
He needs Elvish medicine.

648
01:04:46.663 --> 01:04:47.652
Hurry!

649
01:04:47.864 --> 01:04:51.823
We're six days from Rivendell!
He'll never make it!

650
01:04:52.035 --> 01:04:53.935
Hold on. Frodo.

651
01:04:54.437 --> 01:04:56.496
Gandalf!

652
01:07:27.724 --> 01:07:30.625
Mr. Frodo? He's going cold.

653
01:07:33.496 --> 01:07:35.259
Is he going to die?

654
01:07:35.465 --> 01:07:40.334
He's passing into the Shadow World.
He'll soon become a Wraith like them.

655
01:07:45.441 --> 01:07:49.241
- They're close.
- Sam. do you know the Athelas plant?

656
01:07:49.445 --> 01:07:50.912
- Athelas?
- Kingsfoil.

657
01:07:51.114 --> 01:07:52.172
Kingsfoil. aye. it's a weed.

658
01:07:52.348 --> 01:07:55.545
It may help to slow the poisoning.
Hurry!

659
01:08:09.899 --> 01:08:14.131
What's this?
A Ranger caught off his guard?

660
01:08:38.961 --> 01:08:39.950
Frodo.

661
01:08:41.964 --> 01:08:44.990
I am Arwen - I've come to help you.

662
01:08:47.470 --> 01:08:49.301
Hear my voice...

663
01:08:49.572 --> 01:08:51.699
Come back to the light.

664
01:08:56.879 --> 01:08:58.744
Who is she?

665
01:08:59.382 --> 01:09:01.179
Frodo.

666
01:09:01.384 --> 01:09:04.876
- She's an Elf.
- He's fading.

667
01:09:07.156 --> 01:09:09.351
He's not going to last.

668
01:09:09.559 --> 01:09:12.221
We must get him to my father.

669
01:09:12.929 --> 01:09:15.830
- I've been looking for you for two days.
- Where are you taking him?

670
01:09:16.032 --> 01:09:22.130
There are five Wraiths behind you.
Where the other four are. I do not know.

671
01:09:23.172 --> 01:09:25.572
Stay with the Hobbits -
I'll send horses for you.

672
01:09:25.775 --> 01:09:27.436
I'm the faster rider - I'll take him.

673
01:09:28.344 --> 01:09:29.675
The Road is too dangerous.

674
01:09:29.879 --> 01:09:31.210
What are they saying?

675
01:09:31.414 --> 01:09:33.405
If I can get across the river...

676
01:09:33.616 --> 01:09:36.244
...the power of my people
will protect him.

677
01:09:37.320 --> 01:09:38.912
I do not fear them.

678
01:09:48.798 --> 01:09:50.197
Arwen...

679
01:09:50.399 --> 01:09:53.596
...ride hard. Don't look back.

680
01:09:58.641 --> 01:10:02.975
What are you doing?!
Those Wraiths are still out there!

681
01:11:57.627 --> 01:12:00.357
Give up the halfling. She-Elf.

682
01:12:01.297 --> 01:12:03.857
If you want him. come and claim him.

683
01:12:57.753 --> 01:13:00.221
No. No!

684
01:13:03.526 --> 01:13:05.790
Frodo. no.

685
01:13:05.995 --> 01:13:08.293
Frodo. don't give in.

686
01:13:08.497 --> 01:13:10.488
Not now.

687
01:13:21.410 --> 01:13:23.901
What grace is given me...

688
01:13:24.580 --> 01:13:26.445
...let it pass to him.

689
01:13:26.649 --> 01:13:28.810
Let him be spared.

690
01:13:29.418 --> 01:13:31.477
Save him.

691
01:13:43.899 --> 01:13:49.064
- Where am I?
- You are in the house of Elrond.

692
01:13:49.505 --> 01:13:56.001
And it is 1 0:00 in the morning
on October 24th. if you want to know.

693
01:13:57.947 --> 01:14:01.713
- Gandalf!
- Yes. I'm here.

694
01:14:03.419 --> 01:14:06.445
And you're lucky to be here too.

695
01:14:07.123 --> 01:14:11.150
A few more hours and you
would have been beyond our aid.

696
01:14:11.360 --> 01:14:15.456
But you have some strength in you.
my dear Hobbit.

697
01:14:23.105 --> 01:14:25.596
What happened. Gandalf?

698
01:14:26.542 --> 01:14:31.946
- Why didn't you meet us?
- I am sorry. Frodo.

699
01:14:36.652 --> 01:14:38.415
I was delayed.

700
01:14:39.288 --> 01:14:43.486
A friendship with Saruman
is not lightly thrown aside.

701
01:14:47.596 --> 01:14:52.226
One ill turn deserves another.
It is over.

702
01:14:52.568 --> 01:14:55.264
Embrace the power of the Ring...

703
01:14:55.838 --> 01:14:58.398
...or embrace your own destruction!

704
01:15:00.676 --> 01:15:04.578
There is only one Lord of the Ring.

705
01:15:04.780 --> 01:15:08.773
Only one who can bend it to his will.

706
01:15:09.652 --> 01:15:13.588
And he does not share power.

707
01:15:27.937 --> 01:15:31.270
So you have chosen death.

708
01:15:41.350 --> 01:15:45.150
Gandalf? What is it?

709
01:15:46.121 --> 01:15:47.918
Nothing. Frodo.

710
01:15:48.557 --> 01:15:50.491
Frodo!

711
01:15:51.861 --> 01:15:54.261
- Sam.
- Bless you. you're awake!

712
01:15:54.463 --> 01:15:57.193
Sam has hardly left your side.

713
01:15:57.399 --> 01:15:59.594
We were that worried about you.
Weren't we. Mr. Gandalf?

714
01:15:59.969 --> 01:16:05.066
By the skills of Lord Elrond.
you're beginning to mend.

715
01:16:06.609 --> 01:16:10.170
Welcome to Rivendell. Frodo Baggins.

716
01:16:58.260 --> 01:17:01.559
- Bilbo!
- Hello. Frodo. my lad.

717
01:17:01.730 --> 01:17:03.425
Bilbo.

718
01:17:08.304 --> 01:17:10.204
"There and Back Again:

719
01:17:10.406 --> 01:17:13.204
A Hobbit's Tale. by Bilbo Baggins."

720
01:17:16.278 --> 01:17:19.805
- This is wonderful.
- I meant to go back...

721
01:17:20.149 --> 01:17:23.949
...wonder at the powers of Mirkwood...

722
01:17:24.386 --> 01:17:26.718
...visit Lake-town...

723
01:17:26.922 --> 01:17:30.323
...see the Lonely Mountain again.

724
01:17:30.759 --> 01:17:35.696
But age. it seems.
has finally caught up with me.

725
01:17:47.810 --> 01:17:49.573
I miss the Shire.

726
01:17:49.979 --> 01:17:55.144
I spent all my childhood pretending
I was off somewhere else.

727
01:17:55.417 --> 01:17:59.046
Off with you.
on one of your adventures.

728
01:18:01.957 --> 01:18:05.586
But my own adventure turned out
to be quite different.

729
01:18:10.799 --> 01:18:13.996
I'm not like you. Bilbo.

730
01:18:15.170 --> 01:18:17.434
My dear boy.

731
01:18:21.543 --> 01:18:25.502
- Now. what have I forgotten?
- Packed already?

732
01:18:26.315 --> 01:18:28.112
No harm in being prepared.

733
01:18:28.317 --> 01:18:30.877
- I thought you wanted to see the Elves.
- I do.

734
01:18:31.086 --> 01:18:33.953
- More than anything.
- I did.

735
01:18:34.156 --> 01:18:36.056
It's just...

736
01:18:36.859 --> 01:18:39.453
We did what Gandalf wanted. didn't we?

737
01:18:39.661 --> 01:18:43.324
We got the Ring this far.
to Rivendell. And I thought...

738
01:18:43.532 --> 01:18:46.831
...seeing as how you're on the mend.
we'd be off soon.

739
01:18:47.036 --> 01:18:48.731
Off home.

740
01:18:52.908 --> 01:18:54.899
You are right. Sam.

741
01:18:57.079 --> 01:18:59.843
We did what we set out to do.

742
01:19:00.449 --> 01:19:02.974
The Ring will be safe in Rivendell.

743
01:19:07.122 --> 01:19:09.454
I am ready to go home.

744
01:19:10.192 --> 01:19:12.251
His strength returns.

745
01:19:12.461 --> 01:19:18.161
That wound will never fully heal.
He will carry it the rest of his life.

746
01:19:18.734 --> 01:19:21.259
And yet to have come so far
still bearing the Ring...

747
01:19:21.470 --> 01:19:25.167
...the Hobbit has shown extraordinary
resilience to its evil.

748
01:19:25.374 --> 01:19:28.741
It is a burden he should never
have had to bear.

749
01:19:28.944 --> 01:19:34.382
- We can ask no more of Frodo.
- Gandalf. the enemy is moving.

750
01:19:34.583 --> 01:19:39.247
Sauron's forces are massing in the East.
His Eye is fixed on Rivendell.

751
01:19:39.455 --> 01:19:42.219
And Saruman. you tell me. has betrayed us.

752
01:19:42.424 --> 01:19:45.655
Our list of allies grows thin.

753
01:19:46.395 --> 01:19:49.193
His treachery runs deeper
than you know.

754
01:19:49.398 --> 01:19:53.027
By foul craft. Saruman
has crossed Orcs with Goblin-men.

755
01:19:53.235 --> 01:19:55.703
He's breeding an army
in the caverns of Isengard.

756
01:19:56.004 --> 01:20:00.566
An army that can move in sunlight
and cover great distance at speed.

757
01:20:00.776 --> 01:20:03.176
Saruman is coming for the Ring.

758
01:20:03.579 --> 01:20:07.675
This evil cannot be concealed
by the power of the Elves.

759
01:20:07.883 --> 01:20:12.252
We do not have the strength
to fight both Mordor and Isengard!

760
01:20:16.058 --> 01:20:17.184
Gandalf...

761
01:20:18.494 --> 01:20:21.054
...the Ring cannot stay here.

762
01:20:40.582 --> 01:20:43.813
This peril belongs
to all Middle-earth.

763
01:20:44.019 --> 01:20:46.749
They must decide now how to end it.

764
01:20:47.823 --> 01:20:51.350
The time of the Elves is over.
My people are leaving these shores.

765
01:20:52.027 --> 01:20:55.622
Who will you look to when we've gone?
The Dwarves?

766
01:20:55.831 --> 01:21:00.928
They hide in mountains seeking riches.
They care not for the troubles of others.

767
01:21:02.571 --> 01:21:05.369
It is in Men
that we must place our hope.

768
01:21:05.707 --> 01:21:07.436
Men?

769
01:21:08.310 --> 01:21:11.541
Men are weak.
The race of Men is failing.

770
01:21:11.747 --> 01:21:16.150
The blood of N�menor is all but spent.
its pride and dignity forgotten.

771
01:21:16.518 --> 01:21:19.976
It is because of Men
the Ring survives.

772
01:21:20.189 --> 01:21:21.816
I was there. Gandalf.

773
01:21:22.491 --> 01:21:25.324
I was there 3000 years ago...

774
01:21:32.134 --> 01:21:34.568
...when Isildur took the Ring.

775
01:21:34.770 --> 01:21:38.638
I was there the day
the strength of Men failed.

776
01:21:41.176 --> 01:21:43.736
Isildur. hurry! Follow me.

777
01:21:45.347 --> 01:21:48.976
I led Isildur into the heart
of Mount Doom...

778
01:21:49.184 --> 01:21:52.745
...where the Ring was forged.
the one place it could be destroyed.

779
01:21:52.955 --> 01:21:55.515
Cast it into the fire!

780
01:22:00.662 --> 01:22:04.496
- Destroy it!
- No.

781
01:22:05.834 --> 01:22:07.995
Isildur!

782
01:22:08.470 --> 01:22:13.169
It should have ended that day.
but evil was allowed to endure.

783
01:22:17.312 --> 01:22:21.544
Isildur kept the Ring.
The line of kings is broken.

784
01:22:22.484 --> 01:22:26.113
There's no strength left
in the world of Men.

785
01:22:26.321 --> 01:22:31.156
- They're scattered. divided. leaderless.
- There is one who could unite them.

786
01:22:31.360 --> 01:22:34.693
One who could reclaim
the throne of Gondor.

787
01:22:36.431 --> 01:22:40.197
He turned from that path
a long time ago.

788
01:22:40.402 --> 01:22:42.529
He has chosen exile.

789
01:23:15.404 --> 01:23:18.305
The shards of Narsil.

790
01:23:21.810 --> 01:23:26.270
The blade that cut the Ring
from Sauron's hand.

791
01:23:29.151 --> 01:23:31.415
It's still sharp.

792
01:23:40.329 --> 01:23:43.389
But no more than a broken heirloom.

793
01:24:10.192 --> 01:24:13.252
Why do you fear the past?

794
01:24:14.129 --> 01:24:19.499
You are Isildur's heir.
not Isildur himself.

795
01:24:19.701 --> 01:24:23.137
You are not bound to his fate.

796
01:24:23.672 --> 01:24:27.631
The same blood flows in my veins.

797
01:24:30.679 --> 01:24:33.204
The same weakness.

798
01:24:35.917 --> 01:24:38.715
Your time will come.

799
01:24:38.920 --> 01:24:43.357
You will face the same evil.
And you will defeat it.

800
01:24:46.528 --> 01:24:48.860
The Shadow does not hold sway yet.

801
01:24:49.931 --> 01:24:53.526
Not over you... not over me.

802
01:25:04.913 --> 01:25:08.110
Do you remember when we first met?

803
01:25:11.653 --> 01:25:16.147
I thought I had strayed into a dream.

804
01:25:16.758 --> 01:25:19.249
Long years have passed.

805
01:25:20.962 --> 01:25:24.295
You did not have the cares
you carry now.

806
01:25:25.801 --> 01:25:27.792
Do you remember what I told you?

807
01:25:33.875 --> 01:25:36.571
You said you'd bind yourself to me...

808
01:25:38.613 --> 01:25:43.573
...forsaking the immortal life
of your people.

809
01:25:44.686 --> 01:25:46.654
And to that I hold.

810
01:25:46.855 --> 01:25:50.450
I would rather share
one lifetime with you...

811
01:25:50.659 --> 01:25:54.527
...than face all the Ages
of this world alone.

812
01:26:03.305 --> 01:26:06.763
I choose a mortal life.

813
01:26:08.109 --> 01:26:12.375
- You cannot give me this.
- It is mine to give to whom I will...

814
01:26:15.584 --> 01:26:18.109
...like my heart.

815
01:26:33.869 --> 01:26:37.566
Strangers from distant lands.
friends of old...

816
01:26:37.772 --> 01:26:41.731
...you've been summoned here
to answer the threat of Mordor.

817
01:26:42.344 --> 01:26:47.247
Middle-earth stands upon the brink
of destruction. None can escape it.

818
01:26:47.449 --> 01:26:50.976
You will unite. or you will fall.

819
01:26:51.186 --> 01:26:55.452
Each race is bound to this fate.
this one doom.

820
01:26:57.325 --> 01:27:00.817
Bring forth the Ring. Frodo.

821
01:27:14.876 --> 01:27:16.571
So it is true.

822
01:27:29.958 --> 01:27:34.190
- The doom of Man.
- It is a gift.

823
01:27:35.397 --> 01:27:37.490
A gift to the foes of Mordor.

824
01:27:38.066 --> 01:27:40.534
Why not use this Ring?

825
01:27:41.036 --> 01:27:43.800
Long has my father.
the Steward of Gondor...

826
01:27:44.005 --> 01:27:48.101
...kept the forces of Mordor at bay.
By the blood of our people...

827
01:27:48.276 --> 01:27:50.540
...are your lands kept safe.

828
01:27:52.280 --> 01:27:56.683
Give Gondor the weapon of the enemy.
Let us use it against him.

829
01:27:56.885 --> 01:28:00.651
You cannot wield it.
None of us can.

830
01:28:01.222 --> 01:28:05.318
The One Ring answers to Sauron alone.
It has no other master.

831
01:28:05.527 --> 01:28:09.054
And what would a Ranger know
of this matter?

832
01:28:09.364 --> 01:28:11.355
This is no mere Ranger.

833
01:28:12.334 --> 01:28:15.997
He is Aragorn. son of Arathorn.

834
01:28:16.471 --> 01:28:19.406
You owe him your allegiance.

835
01:28:23.511 --> 01:28:25.411
Aragorn.

836
01:28:27.215 --> 01:28:29.979
This is Isildur's heir?

837
01:28:32.320 --> 01:28:35.084
And heir to the throne of Gondor.

838
01:28:37.158 --> 01:28:38.557
Sit down. Legolas.

839
01:28:41.963 --> 01:28:44.796
Gondor has no king.

840
01:28:46.668 --> 01:28:48.397
Gondor needs no king.

841
01:28:55.076 --> 01:28:58.739
Aragorn is right. We cannot use it.

842
01:28:59.748 --> 01:29:03.240
You have only one choice.

843
01:29:03.451 --> 01:29:05.783
The Ring must be destroyed.

844
01:29:11.026 --> 01:29:13.620
What are we waiting for?

845
01:29:25.740 --> 01:29:28.766
The Ring cannot be destroyed. Gimli.
son of Gl�in...

846
01:29:28.977 --> 01:29:33.175
...by any craft that we here possess.

847
01:29:33.748 --> 01:29:37.844
The Ring was made in the fires
of Mount Doom.

848
01:29:38.053 --> 01:29:41.887
Only there can it be unmade.

849
01:29:42.991 --> 01:29:45.585
It must be taken deep into Mordor...

850
01:29:45.794 --> 01:29:50.754
...and cast back into the fiery chasm
from whence it came.

851
01:29:52.734 --> 01:29:54.759
One of you...

852
01:29:55.270 --> 01:29:57.431
...must do this.

853
01:30:00.341 --> 01:30:04.038
One does not simply walk into Mordor.

854
01:30:04.979 --> 01:30:08.608
Its Black Gates are guarded
by more than just Orcs.

855
01:30:09.417 --> 01:30:13.547
There is evil there
that does not sleep.

856
01:30:13.755 --> 01:30:18.021
The Great Eye is ever-watchful.

857
01:30:18.760 --> 01:30:20.819
It is a barren wasteland...

858
01:30:21.029 --> 01:30:24.624
...riddled with fire. and ash
and dust.

859
01:30:24.833 --> 01:30:28.667
The very air you breathe
is a poisonous fume.

860
01:30:28.870 --> 01:30:33.170
Not with 1 0.000 men
could you do this. It is folly.

861
01:30:33.374 --> 01:30:37.868
Have you heard nothing Lord Elrond
has said? The Ring must be destroyed.

862
01:30:38.046 --> 01:30:40.640
And I suppose you think
you are the one to do it!

863
01:30:40.849 --> 01:30:45.513
And if we fail. what then? What happens
when Sauron takes back what is his?

864
01:30:45.720 --> 01:30:50.953
I will be dead before I see the Ring
in the hands of an Elf!

865
01:30:52.994 --> 01:30:55.462
Never trust an Elf!

866
01:30:56.664 --> 01:31:02.466
Do you not understand? While you bicker
amongst yourselves. Sauron's power grows!

867
01:31:02.804 --> 01:31:05.705
None can escape it!
You'll all be destroyed!

868
01:31:24.459 --> 01:31:26.723
I will take it.

869
01:31:28.696 --> 01:31:31.221
I will take it.

870
01:31:37.038 --> 01:31:40.098
I will take the Ring to Mordor.

871
01:31:48.183 --> 01:31:49.445
Though...

872
01:31:52.587 --> 01:31:54.350
...I do not know the way.

873
01:31:56.424 --> 01:32:00.724
I will help you bear
this burden. Frodo Baggins...

874
01:32:00.929 --> 01:32:04.296
...as long as it is yours to bear.

875
01:32:05.433 --> 01:32:08.459
If by my life
or death I can protect you...

876
01:32:09.204 --> 01:32:10.569
...I will.

877
01:32:13.808 --> 01:32:16.106
You have my sword.

878
01:32:17.912 --> 01:32:19.971
And you have my bow.

879
01:32:20.582 --> 01:32:23.050
And my ax.

880
01:32:30.058 --> 01:32:33.084
You carry the fates
of us all. little one.

881
01:32:35.096 --> 01:32:38.759
If this is indeed
the will of the Council...

882
01:32:39.200 --> 01:32:41.668
...then Gondor will see it done.

883
01:32:44.239 --> 01:32:49.006
- Frodo's not going anywhere without me.
- It is hardly possible to separate you...

884
01:32:49.210 --> 01:32:54.113
...even when he is summoned
to a secret Council and you are not.

885
01:32:54.682 --> 01:32:56.582
We're coming too!

886
01:32:58.620 --> 01:33:01.384
You'll have to send us home
tied up in a sack to stop us.

887
01:33:01.589 --> 01:33:04.990
Anyway. you need people
of intelligence on this sort of...

888
01:33:05.326 --> 01:33:06.623
...mission.

889
01:33:06.828 --> 01:33:08.318
Quest.

890
01:33:08.763 --> 01:33:09.752
Thing.

891
01:33:11.666 --> 01:33:14.362
Well. that rules you out. Pip.

892
01:33:15.904 --> 01:33:17.838
Nine companions.

893
01:33:19.641 --> 01:33:21.438
So be it.

894
01:33:21.809 --> 01:33:24.835
You shall be
the Fellowship of the Ring.

895
01:33:25.480 --> 01:33:27.277
Great!

896
01:33:27.548 --> 01:33:29.778
Where are we going?

897
01:33:39.827 --> 01:33:40.987
My old sword!

898
01:33:41.329 --> 01:33:42.921
Sting.

899
01:33:43.131 --> 01:33:44.291
Here. take it. Take it.

900
01:33:49.837 --> 01:33:53.705
- It's so light.
- Yes. Made by the Elves. you know.

901
01:33:54.375 --> 01:33:58.539
The blade glows blue
when Orcs are close.

902
01:33:58.746 --> 01:34:03.342
And it's times like that. my lad.
when you have to be extra careful.

903
01:34:03.551 --> 01:34:06.019
Here's a pretty thing.

904
01:34:06.421 --> 01:34:07.718
Mithril.

905
01:34:08.489 --> 01:34:12.892
As light as a feather.
and as hard as dragon scales.

906
01:34:13.094 --> 01:34:16.359
Let me see you put it on. Come on.

907
01:34:24.405 --> 01:34:26.430
My old ring.

908
01:34:27.675 --> 01:34:31.611
I should very much like...

909
01:34:31.813 --> 01:34:35.840
...to hold it again. one last time.

910
01:34:53.234 --> 01:34:56.863
I'm sorry I brought this upon you.
my boy.

911
01:34:57.238 --> 01:35:01.299
I'm sorry that you
must carry this burden.

912
01:35:05.813 --> 01:35:08.907
I'm sorry for everything.

913
01:36:21.622 --> 01:36:26.059
We must hold to this course. west
of the Misty Mountains. for 40 days.

914
01:36:26.260 --> 01:36:30.026
If our luck holds. the Gap of Rohan
will still be open to us.

915
01:36:30.231 --> 01:36:33.792
From there. our road
turns east to Mordor.

916
01:36:34.001 --> 01:36:37.801
Two. one. five. Good! Very good.

917
01:36:39.540 --> 01:36:40.666
Move your feet.

918
01:36:40.875 --> 01:36:42.206
- You look good. Pippin.
- Thanks.

919
01:36:42.410 --> 01:36:43.843
Faster!

920
01:36:45.179 --> 01:36:48.979
If anyone was to ask for my opinion.
which I note they're not...

921
01:36:49.183 --> 01:36:51.913
...I'd say we were taking
the long way 'round.

922
01:36:52.420 --> 01:36:55.514
Gandalf. we could pass through
the Mines of Moria.

923
01:36:56.124 --> 01:37:00.026
My cousin Balin would give us
a royal welcome.

924
01:37:00.228 --> 01:37:05.564
No. I would not take the road through
Moria unless I had no other choice.

925
01:37:14.742 --> 01:37:15.902
Sorry!

926
01:37:16.611 --> 01:37:18.101
Get him!

927
01:37:19.580 --> 01:37:22.048
- For the Shire!
- Hold him. Hold him down. Merry!

928
01:37:22.250 --> 01:37:23.842
You've got my arm!
You've got my arm!

929
01:37:24.318 --> 01:37:26.946
- What is that?
- Nothing. It's just a wisp of cloud.

930
01:37:27.155 --> 01:37:29.885
It's moving fast.

931
01:37:30.124 --> 01:37:32.285
Against the wind.

932
01:37:33.027 --> 01:37:35.154
- Crebain from Dunland!
- Hide!

933
01:37:35.363 --> 01:37:38.127
- Hurry!
- Take cover!

934
01:38:11.532 --> 01:38:13.261
Spies of Saruman.

935
01:38:14.035 --> 01:38:17.300
The passage south is being watched.

936
01:38:18.439 --> 01:38:21.772
We must take the Pass of Caradhras.

937
01:38:34.388 --> 01:38:36.117
Frodo!

938
01:38:55.076 --> 01:38:57.374
Boromir.

939
01:38:57.578 --> 01:39:01.810
It is a strange fate that we should
suffer so much fear and doubt...

940
01:39:02.016 --> 01:39:05.144
...over so small a thing.

941
01:39:08.356 --> 01:39:10.324
Such a little thing.

942
01:39:10.524 --> 01:39:11.991
Boromir!

943
01:39:12.593 --> 01:39:15.255
Give the Ring to Frodo.

944
01:39:25.106 --> 01:39:27.131
As you wish.

945
01:39:27.875 --> 01:39:29.900
I care not.

946
01:40:05.279 --> 01:40:09.978
So. Gandalf. you tried
to lead them over Caradhras.

947
01:40:10.184 --> 01:40:14.780
And if that fails.
where then will you go?

948
01:40:16.090 --> 01:40:19.059
If the mountain defeats you...

949
01:40:19.260 --> 01:40:23.697
...will you risk
a more dangerous road?

950
01:40:36.077 --> 01:40:38.978
There is a fell voice on the air.

951
01:40:40.081 --> 01:40:41.571
It's Saruman!

952
01:40:50.491 --> 01:40:55.155
He's trying to bring down the mountain!
Gandalf. we must turn back!

953
01:40:55.363 --> 01:40:57.194
No!

954
01:42:03.631 --> 01:42:05.462
We must get off the mountain!

955
01:42:05.933 --> 01:42:10.302
Make for the Gap of Rohan.
and take the west road to my city!

956
01:42:10.504 --> 01:42:13.871
The Gap of Rohan takes us
too close to Isengard!

957
01:42:14.074 --> 01:42:17.771
We cannot pass over a mountain.
Let us go under it.

958
01:42:17.978 --> 01:42:20.845
Let us go through the Mines of Moria.

959
01:42:22.683 --> 01:42:26.483
Moria. You fear to go
into those mines.

960
01:42:27.154 --> 01:42:32.217
The Dwarves delved too greedily
and too deep.

961
01:42:33.027 --> 01:42:37.896
You know what they awoke
in the darkness of Khazad-d�m:

962
01:42:39.166 --> 01:42:42.693
Shadow and flame.

963
01:42:46.040 --> 01:42:48.770
Let the Ring-bearer decide.

964
01:42:54.114 --> 01:42:55.775
Frodo?

965
01:42:58.819 --> 01:43:01.686
We will go through the mines.

966
01:43:02.490 --> 01:43:04.424
So be it.

967
01:43:12.500 --> 01:43:13.865
The walls...

968
01:43:14.535 --> 01:43:16.628
...of Moria.

969
01:43:25.379 --> 01:43:28.712
Well. let's see.

970
01:43:28.916 --> 01:43:30.281
Ithildin.

971
01:43:30.918 --> 01:43:34.285
It mirrors only starlight
and moonlight.

972
01:43:48.335 --> 01:43:52.396
It reads. "The Doors of Durin.
Lord of Moria.

973
01:43:53.007 --> 01:43:57.637
- Speak. friend. and enter."
- What do you suppose that means?

974
01:43:57.845 --> 01:44:02.578
It's simple. If you are a friend. you speak
the password and the doors will open.

975
01:44:33.781 --> 01:44:36.341
Mines are no place for a pony.

976
01:44:36.550 --> 01:44:40.646
- Even one so brave as Bill.
- Bye-bye. Bill.

977
01:44:41.822 --> 01:44:44.586
Go on. Bill. Go on.

978
01:44:45.159 --> 01:44:48.686
Don't worry. Sam.
he knows the way home.

979
01:44:55.469 --> 01:44:58.063
Do not disturb the water.

980
01:44:58.272 --> 01:45:00.172
Oh. it's useless.

981
01:45:12.820 --> 01:45:15.015
It's a riddle.

982
01:45:17.758 --> 01:45:20.886
"Speak 'friend' and enter."

983
01:45:21.261 --> 01:45:24.162
What's the Elvish word for "friend"?

984
01:45:25.633 --> 01:45:26.930
Mellon.

985
01:45:44.985 --> 01:45:49.854
Soon. Master Elf. you will enjoy
the fabled hospitality of the Dwarves.

986
01:45:50.324 --> 01:45:56.024
Roaring fires. malt beer.
ripe meat off the bone!

987
01:45:57.564 --> 01:46:00.624
This. my friend.
is the home of my cousin Balin.

988
01:46:00.968 --> 01:46:03.402
And they call it a mine.

989
01:46:03.604 --> 01:46:05.538
A mine!

990
01:46:06.607 --> 01:46:09.940
This is no mine. It's a tomb.

991
01:46:16.083 --> 01:46:17.641
No...

992
01:46:18.919 --> 01:46:20.546
No!

993
01:46:23.190 --> 01:46:24.748
Goblins.

994
01:46:28.662 --> 01:46:32.962
We make for the Gap of Rohan.
We should never have come here.

995
01:46:34.001 --> 01:46:36.595
Now. get out of here. Get out!

996
01:46:39.373 --> 01:46:41.773
- Frodo!
- Help!

997
01:46:41.975 --> 01:46:43.567
Strider!

998
01:46:43.777 --> 01:46:46.575
- Help!
- Get off him!

999
01:46:46.780 --> 01:46:47.769
Aragorn!

1000
01:46:58.192 --> 01:46:59.181
Frodo!

1001
01:47:25.552 --> 01:47:26.610
Into the mines!

1002
01:47:26.820 --> 01:47:30.017
- Legolas!
- Into the cave!

1003
01:47:34.294 --> 01:47:36.057
Run!

1004
01:47:53.280 --> 01:47:56.545
We now have but one choice.

1005
01:47:56.750 --> 01:48:01.619
We must face the long dark of Moria.

1006
01:48:01.889 --> 01:48:03.857
Be on your guard.

1007
01:48:04.057 --> 01:48:07.493
There are older
and fouler things than Orcs...

1008
01:48:07.694 --> 01:48:11.221
...in the deep places of the world.

1009
01:48:19.173 --> 01:48:23.109
Quietly now. It's a four-day journey
to the other side.

1010
01:48:23.310 --> 01:48:27.144
Let us hope that our presence
may go unnoticed.

1011
01:48:51.572 --> 01:48:53.267
Pippin.

1012
01:49:13.627 --> 01:49:16.562
I have no memory of this place.

1013
01:49:18.632 --> 01:49:20.065
- Are we lost?
- No.

1014
01:49:20.267 --> 01:49:22.792
- I think we are.
- Gandalf's thinking.

1015
01:49:23.003 --> 01:49:24.470
- Merry?
- What?

1016
01:49:24.671 --> 01:49:26.571
I'm hungry.

1017
01:49:37.918 --> 01:49:42.378
- There's something down there.
- It's Gollum.

1018
01:49:42.589 --> 01:49:46.719
- Gollum?
- He's been following us for three days.

1019
01:49:46.927 --> 01:49:51.091
- He escaped the dungeons of Barad-d�r?
- Escaped...

1020
01:49:51.832 --> 01:49:53.459
...or was set loose.

1021
01:49:59.640 --> 01:50:04.771
He hates and loves the Ring.
as he hates and loves himself.

1022
01:50:04.978 --> 01:50:07.538
He will never be rid of his need for it.

1023
01:50:07.848 --> 01:50:10.715
It's a pity Bilbo didn't kill him
when he had the chance.

1024
01:50:10.918 --> 01:50:12.146
Pity?

1025
01:50:13.186 --> 01:50:16.121
It is pity that stayed Bilbo's hand.

1026
01:50:17.024 --> 01:50:22.223
Many that live deserve death.
Some that die deserve life.

1027
01:50:23.697 --> 01:50:26.165
Can you give it to them. Frodo?

1028
01:50:28.568 --> 01:50:32.527
Do not be too eager
to deal out death and judgment.

1029
01:50:32.739 --> 01:50:35.674
Even the very wise
cannot see all ends.

1030
01:50:36.243 --> 01:50:42.148
My heart tells me that Gollum has some
part to play yet. for good or ill...

1031
01:50:42.950 --> 01:50:45.817
...before this is over.

1032
01:50:47.321 --> 01:50:51.189
The pity of Bilbo
may rule the fate of many.

1033
01:50:57.864 --> 01:51:01.163
I wish the Ring
had never come to me.

1034
01:51:02.602 --> 01:51:04.661
I wish none of this had happened.

1035
01:51:04.871 --> 01:51:09.899
So do all who live to see such times.
But that is not for them to decide.

1036
01:51:10.677 --> 01:51:16.172
All we have to decide is what to do
with the time that is given to us.

1037
01:51:17.684 --> 01:51:21.711
There are other forces at work in this
world. Frodo. besides the will of evil.

1038
01:51:22.089 --> 01:51:24.557
Bilbo was meant to find the Ring.

1039
01:51:25.025 --> 01:51:29.359
In which case.
you also were meant to have it.

1040
01:51:29.563 --> 01:51:32.726
And that is an encouraging thought.

1041
01:51:37.604 --> 01:51:39.538
It's that way.

1042
01:51:39.740 --> 01:51:42.004
- He's remembered.
- No.

1043
01:51:42.209 --> 01:51:46.009
But the air doesn't smell
so foul down here.

1044
01:51:46.213 --> 01:51:51.446
If in doubt. Meriadoc.
always follow your nose.

1045
01:52:06.266 --> 01:52:10.430
Let me risk a little more light.

1046
01:52:15.042 --> 01:52:17.135
Behold...

1047
01:52:17.544 --> 01:52:22.811
...the great realm
and Dwarf-city of Dwarrowdelf.

1048
01:52:25.252 --> 01:52:28.688
There's an eye opener. and no mistake.

1049
01:52:53.647 --> 01:52:55.342
Gimli!

1050
01:53:02.756 --> 01:53:04.383
No!

1051
01:53:06.993 --> 01:53:10.156
Oh. no.

1052
01:53:11.965 --> 01:53:13.227
No.

1053
01:53:20.540 --> 01:53:22.531
"Here lies Balin...

1054
01:53:22.976 --> 01:53:24.967
...son of Fundin...

1055
01:53:25.278 --> 01:53:27.906
...Lord of Moria."

1056
01:53:28.982 --> 01:53:30.677
He is dead. then.

1057
01:53:32.419 --> 01:53:34.114
It's as I feared.

1058
01:53:52.372 --> 01:53:55.273
We must move on. We cannot linger.

1059
01:53:55.475 --> 01:54:00.174
"They have taken the bridge
and the second hall.

1060
01:54:01.281 --> 01:54:03.875
We have barred the gates...

1061
01:54:04.551 --> 01:54:07.019
...but cannot hold them for long.

1062
01:54:07.220 --> 01:54:10.018
The ground shakes.

1063
01:54:10.457 --> 01:54:12.015
Drums...

1064
01:54:12.425 --> 01:54:15.792
...drums in the deep.

1065
01:54:19.332 --> 01:54:21.357
We cannot get out.

1066
01:54:23.403 --> 01:54:27.203
A Shadow moves in the dark.

1067
01:54:28.875 --> 01:54:31.469
We cannot get out.

1068
01:54:34.481 --> 01:54:36.381
They are coming."

1069
01:55:19.426 --> 01:55:21.291
Fool of a Took!

1070
01:55:21.661 --> 01:55:25.461
Throw yourself in next time.
and rid us of your stupidity.

1071
01:55:51.358 --> 01:55:53.053
Frodo!

1072
01:55:55.362 --> 01:55:56.795
Orcs.

1073
01:56:03.837 --> 01:56:05.828
Get back! Stay close to Gandalf!

1074
01:56:13.046 --> 01:56:14.877
They have a cave-troll.

1075
01:56:30.697 --> 01:56:31.823
Let them come!

1076
01:56:32.365 --> 01:56:35.892
There is one Dwarf yet in Moria
who still draws breath.

1077
01:58:26.379 --> 01:58:29.143
I think I'm getting the hang of this.

1078
01:58:33.887 --> 01:58:35.616
Frodo!

1079
01:59:09.189 --> 01:59:11.054
Aragorn! Aragorn!

1080
01:59:12.058 --> 01:59:13.923
Frodo!

1081
01:59:59.105 --> 02:00:00.970
Frodo!

1082
02:01:01.200 --> 02:01:02.497
Oh. no.

1083
02:01:10.877 --> 02:01:12.811
He's alive.

1084
02:01:15.248 --> 02:01:18.217
I'm all right. I'm not hurt.

1085
02:01:18.418 --> 02:01:20.648
You should be dead.

1086
02:01:20.853 --> 02:01:23.344
That spear would have skewered
a wild boar.

1087
02:01:23.556 --> 02:01:28.289
I think there's more to this Hobbit
than meets the eye.

1088
02:01:34.200 --> 02:01:35.224
Mithril.

1089
02:01:38.037 --> 02:01:40.631
You are full of surprises.
Master Baggins.

1090
02:01:46.679 --> 02:01:48.579
To the Bridge of Khazad-d�m!

1091
02:02:03.563 --> 02:02:05.224
This way!

1092
02:03:15.601 --> 02:03:18.570
What is this new devilry?

1093
02:03:34.654 --> 02:03:37.418
A Balrog.

1094
02:03:37.790 --> 02:03:40.884
A demon of the ancient world.

1095
02:03:43.129 --> 02:03:45.529
This foe is beyond any of you.

1096
02:03:46.699 --> 02:03:48.257
Run!

1097
02:03:55.641 --> 02:03:57.108
Quickly!

1098
02:04:13.726 --> 02:04:15.023
Gandalf.

1099
02:04:15.628 --> 02:04:17.220
Lead them on. Aragorn.

1100
02:04:18.664 --> 02:04:21.155
The bridge is near.

1101
02:04:23.202 --> 02:04:27.332
Do as I say!
Swords are no more use here.

1102
02:04:56.435 --> 02:04:58.198
Gandalf!

1103
02:05:16.455 --> 02:05:17.683
Merry! Pippin!

1104
02:05:28.801 --> 02:05:30.325
Sam!

1105
02:05:33.072 --> 02:05:36.303
Nobody tosses a Dwarf.

1106
02:05:39.345 --> 02:05:40.778
Not the beard!

1107
02:05:53.993 --> 02:05:55.927
Steady.

1108
02:05:57.997 --> 02:05:59.658
Hold on!

1109
02:06:20.720 --> 02:06:21.914
Hang on!

1110
02:06:32.698 --> 02:06:34.461
Lean forward!

1111
02:06:37.470 --> 02:06:38.494
Steady.

1112
02:06:39.805 --> 02:06:40.965
Come on!

1113
02:06:41.173 --> 02:06:42.663
Now!

1114
02:06:59.859 --> 02:07:01.690
Over the bridge!

1115
02:07:01.894 --> 02:07:03.486
Fly!

1116
02:07:48.107 --> 02:07:50.166
You cannot pass!

1117
02:07:50.376 --> 02:07:51.934
Gandalf!

1118
02:07:56.215 --> 02:08:01.084
I am a servant of the Secret Fire.
wielder of the flame of Anor.

1119
02:08:02.088 --> 02:08:05.888
The dark fire will not avail you.
flame of Ud�n!

1120
02:08:15.835 --> 02:08:17.803
Go back to the Shadow.

1121
02:08:25.644 --> 02:08:30.104
You shall not pass!

1122
02:08:57.243 --> 02:09:01.145
- No! No!
- Gandalf!

1123
02:09:08.821 --> 02:09:11.255
Fly. you fools!

1124
02:09:15.394 --> 02:09:17.555
No!

1125
02:09:23.702 --> 02:09:25.863
Aragorn!

1126
02:10:23.162 --> 02:10:25.960
Legolas. get them up.

1127
02:10:30.069 --> 02:10:31.934
Give them a moment. for pity's sake!

1128
02:10:32.138 --> 02:10:35.767
By nightfall. these hills will
be swarming with Orcs.

1129
02:10:35.975 --> 02:10:39.308
We must reach the woods of Lothl�rien.

1130
02:10:40.246 --> 02:10:43.511
Come. Boromir. Legolas.
Gimli. get them up.

1131
02:10:45.017 --> 02:10:47.247
On your feet. Sam.

1132
02:10:47.586 --> 02:10:49.076
Frodo?

1133
02:10:51.123 --> 02:10:52.818
Frodo!

1134
02:11:45.344 --> 02:11:47.869
Stay close. young Hobbits!

1135
02:11:48.647 --> 02:11:52.777
They say that a great sorceress
lives in these woods.

1136
02:11:52.985 --> 02:11:55.510
An Elf-witch...

1137
02:11:56.055 --> 02:11:58.922
...of terrible power.

1138
02:11:59.491 --> 02:12:01.686
All who look upon her...

1139
02:12:01.894 --> 02:12:03.691
...fall under her spell.

1140
02:12:03.896 --> 02:12:05.193
Frodo!

1141
02:12:07.433 --> 02:12:09.492
And are never seen again.

1142
02:12:09.702 --> 02:12:14.196
Your coming to us is
as the footsteps of doom.

1143
02:12:14.406 --> 02:12:18.137
You bring great evil here.
Ring-bearer.

1144
02:12:18.344 --> 02:12:20.073
Mr. Frodo?

1145
02:12:25.384 --> 02:12:30.981
Well. here's one Dwarf
she won't ensnare so easily.

1146
02:12:31.190 --> 02:12:35.718
I have the eyes of a hawk
and the ears of a fox.

1147
02:12:43.402 --> 02:12:47.998
The Dwarf breathes so loud.
we could have shot him in the dark.

1148
02:12:49.742 --> 02:12:51.209
Haldir of Lorien.

1149
02:12:51.810 --> 02:12:53.801
We come here for help.

1150
02:12:55.347 --> 02:12:57.076
We need your protection.

1151
02:12:57.283 --> 02:13:01.515
Aragorn. these woods are perilous.
We should go back.

1152
02:13:01.720 --> 02:13:07.625
You have entered the realm of the Lady
of the Wood. You cannot go back.

1153
02:13:10.029 --> 02:13:13.521
Come. She is waiting.

1154
02:14:20.599 --> 02:14:25.002
Eight there are here. yet nine there
were set out from Rivendell.

1155
02:14:25.270 --> 02:14:27.067
Tell me. where is Gandalf?

1156
02:14:27.272 --> 02:14:31.174
For I much desire to speak with him.

1157
02:14:32.811 --> 02:14:36.008
He has fallen into Shadow.

1158
02:14:40.853 --> 02:14:43.913
The quest stands upon the edge
of a knife.

1159
02:14:44.757 --> 02:14:47.749
Stray but a little and it will fail...

1160
02:14:48.127 --> 02:14:50.960
...to the ruin of all.

1161
02:15:04.710 --> 02:15:09.306
Yet hope remains
while the Company is true.

1162
02:15:12.618 --> 02:15:17.282
Do not let your hearts be troubled.
Go now and rest...

1163
02:15:17.856 --> 02:15:21.383
...for you are weary with sorrow
and much toil.

1164
02:15:23.862 --> 02:15:25.796
Tonight. you will sleep...

1165
02:15:25.998 --> 02:15:29.365
Welcome. Frodo of the Shire...

1166
02:15:30.669 --> 02:15:32.694
...one who has seen the Eye!

1167
02:15:47.453 --> 02:15:49.887
A lament for Gandalf.

1168
02:15:51.824 --> 02:15:54.156
What do they say about him?

1169
02:15:54.359 --> 02:15:59.490
I have not the heart to tell you.
For me. the grief is still too near.

1170
02:16:02.201 --> 02:16:04.465
Take some rest.

1171
02:16:04.937 --> 02:16:07.599
These borders are well-protected.

1172
02:16:07.806 --> 02:16:10.366
I will find no rest here.

1173
02:16:13.178 --> 02:16:16.170
I heard her voice inside my head.

1174
02:16:16.448 --> 02:16:20.145
She spoke of my father
and the fall of Gondor.

1175
02:16:20.352 --> 02:16:25.813
She said to me.
"Even now there is hope left."

1176
02:16:27.226 --> 02:16:30.059
But I cannot see it.

1177
02:16:31.363 --> 02:16:33.854
It is long since we had any hope.

1178
02:16:44.109 --> 02:16:46.236
My father is a noble man.

1179
02:16:46.979 --> 02:16:49.174
But his rule is failing...

1180
02:16:52.317 --> 02:16:54.945
...and our people lose faith.

1181
02:16:56.588 --> 02:16:59.887
He looks to me to make things right.
and I would do it.

1182
02:17:00.092 --> 02:17:03.619
I would see the glory
of Gondor restored.

1183
02:17:06.698 --> 02:17:09.462
Have you ever seen it. Aragorn?

1184
02:17:10.102 --> 02:17:12.297
The White Tower of Ecthelion.

1185
02:17:12.504 --> 02:17:16.133
Glimmering like a spike
of pearl and silver.

1186
02:17:16.808 --> 02:17:20.300
Its banners caught high
in the morning breeze.

1187
02:17:23.181 --> 02:17:25.411
Have you ever been called home...

1188
02:17:25.617 --> 02:17:29.280
...by the clear ringing
of silver trumpets?

1189
02:17:30.188 --> 02:17:33.157
I have seen the White City...

1190
02:17:33.625 --> 02:17:34.990
...Long ago.

1191
02:17:35.961 --> 02:17:40.898
One day. our paths will lead us there.

1192
02:17:41.867 --> 02:17:44.802
And the tower guard
shall take up the call:

1193
02:17:45.237 --> 02:17:48.570
"The Lords of Gondor have returned."

1194
02:18:55.774 --> 02:18:58.334
Will you look into the mirror?

1195
02:18:58.543 --> 02:19:00.067
What will I see?

1196
02:19:03.048 --> 02:19:05.380
Even the wisest cannot tell.

1197
02:19:06.284 --> 02:19:08.115
For the mirror...

1198
02:19:08.320 --> 02:19:10.845
...shows many things.

1199
02:19:13.859 --> 02:19:16.259
Things that were...

1200
02:19:16.461 --> 02:19:19.021
...things that are...

1201
02:19:19.798 --> 02:19:21.766
...and some things...

1202
02:19:25.337 --> 02:19:28.670
...that have not yet come to pass.

1203
02:20:51.223 --> 02:20:54.056
I know what it is you saw.

1204
02:20:56.495 --> 02:20:58.963
For it is also in my mind.

1205
02:21:00.766 --> 02:21:04.827
It is what will come to pass
if you should fail.

1206
02:21:07.205 --> 02:21:12.074
The Fellowship is breaking.
It is already begun.

1207
02:21:12.711 --> 02:21:16.010
He will try to take the Ring.

1208
02:21:16.214 --> 02:21:18.205
You know of whom I speak.

1209
02:21:19.217 --> 02:21:23.881
One by one. it will destroy them all.

1210
02:21:25.390 --> 02:21:27.824
If you ask it of me...

1211
02:21:28.226 --> 02:21:31.286
...I will give you the One Ring.

1212
02:21:32.330 --> 02:21:34.491
You offer it to me freely.

1213
02:21:39.104 --> 02:21:43.040
I do not deny that my heart
has greatly desired this.

1214
02:21:49.414 --> 02:21:52.679
In place of a Dark Lord.
you would have a queen...

1215
02:21:53.151 --> 02:21:56.951
...not dark but beautiful.
and terrible as the dawn!

1216
02:21:57.589 --> 02:22:00.615
Treacherous as the sea!

1217
02:22:01.126 --> 02:22:06.029
Stronger than the foundations
of the earth!

1218
02:22:06.498 --> 02:22:08.898
All shall love me...

1219
02:22:09.100 --> 02:22:11.933
...and despair.

1220
02:22:26.017 --> 02:22:30.351
I pass the test. I will diminish...

1221
02:22:30.622 --> 02:22:33.090
...and go into the West...

1222
02:22:33.291 --> 02:22:37.751
...and remain Galadriel.
- I cannot do this alone.

1223
02:22:41.366 --> 02:22:45.496
You are a Ring-bearer. Frodo.
To bear a Ring of Power...

1224
02:22:46.438 --> 02:22:47.928
...is to be alone.

1225
02:22:48.540 --> 02:22:51.976
This task was appointed to you.

1226
02:22:52.477 --> 02:22:55.674
And if you do not find a way...

1227
02:22:56.548 --> 02:22:58.539
...no one will.

1228
02:22:58.950 --> 02:23:02.078
Then I know what I must do.

1229
02:23:02.787 --> 02:23:03.845
It's just...

1230
02:23:07.092 --> 02:23:09.356
...I'm afraid to do it.

1231
02:23:12.831 --> 02:23:17.962
Even the smallest person can change
the course of the future.

1232
02:23:23.308 --> 02:23:29.042
Do you know how the Orcs
first came into being?

1233
02:23:29.781 --> 02:23:33.148
They were Elves once.

1234
02:23:34.352 --> 02:23:37.685
Taken by the Dark Powers...

1235
02:23:37.889 --> 02:23:41.052
...tortured and mutilated.

1236
02:23:41.393 --> 02:23:46.695
A ruined and terrible form of life.

1237
02:23:46.998 --> 02:23:48.795
And now...

1238
02:23:50.268 --> 02:23:52.168
...perfected.

1239
02:23:52.871 --> 02:23:56.034
My fighting Uruk-hai...

1240
02:23:57.976 --> 02:24:00.308
...whom do you serve?

1241
02:24:00.512 --> 02:24:03.003
Saruman!

1242
02:24:23.835 --> 02:24:27.271
Hunt them down. Do not stop
until they are found.

1243
02:24:27.472 --> 02:24:30.407
You do not know pain.
You do not know fear.

1244
02:24:30.608 --> 02:24:33.577
You will taste Man-flesh!

1245
02:24:38.616 --> 02:24:42.313
One of the halflings carries
something of great value.

1246
02:24:42.487 --> 02:24:46.685
Bring them to me alive and unspoiled.

1247
02:24:48.493 --> 02:24:49.790
Kill the others.

1248
02:25:17.689 --> 02:25:20.886
Farewell. Frodo Baggins.

1249
02:25:21.092 --> 02:25:24.493
I give you the light of E�rendil...

1250
02:25:25.263 --> 02:25:27.595
...our most beloved star.

1251
02:25:39.310 --> 02:25:43.713
May it be a light for you
in dark places...

1252
02:25:43.915 --> 02:25:48.045
...when all other lights go out.

1253
02:27:27.051 --> 02:27:28.382
Frodo.

1254
02:27:30.255 --> 02:27:31.745
The Argonath.

1255
02:27:35.193 --> 02:27:38.924
Long have I desired
to look upon the kings of old.

1256
02:27:39.664 --> 02:27:41.598
My kin.

1257
02:29:00.578 --> 02:29:02.808
We cross the lake at nightfall.

1258
02:29:03.014 --> 02:29:05.574
Hide the boats and continue on foot.

1259
02:29:05.783 --> 02:29:09.241
- We approach Mordor from the North.
- Oh. yes?

1260
02:29:09.621 --> 02:29:13.455
Just a simple matter of finding
our way through Emyn Muil...

1261
02:29:13.658 --> 02:29:16.889
...an impassable labyrinth
of razor-sharp rocks.

1262
02:29:17.095 --> 02:29:20.189
And after that. it gets even better.

1263
02:29:20.598 --> 02:29:25.535
Festering. stinking marshland
as far as the eye can see.

1264
02:29:25.737 --> 02:29:27.136
That is our road.

1265
02:29:28.673 --> 02:29:31.870
I suggest you take some rest
and recover your strength. Master Dwarf.

1266
02:29:32.076 --> 02:29:33.805
Recover my...

1267
02:29:36.848 --> 02:29:38.782
- We should leave now.
- No.

1268
02:29:38.983 --> 02:29:43.420
Orcs patrol the eastern shore.
We must wait for cover of darkness.

1269
02:29:43.621 --> 02:29:47.079
It is not the eastern shore
that worries me.

1270
02:29:47.292 --> 02:29:51.285
A shadow and a threat
has been growing in my mind.

1271
02:29:51.796 --> 02:29:56.028
Something draws near.
I can feel it.

1272
02:29:57.969 --> 02:30:02.929
Recover strength?
Pay no heed to that. young Hobbit.

1273
02:30:03.441 --> 02:30:05.136
Where's Frodo?

1274
02:30:30.802 --> 02:30:32.736
None of us should wander alone.

1275
02:30:34.105 --> 02:30:36.232
You. least of all.

1276
02:30:36.441 --> 02:30:38.875
So much depends on you.

1277
02:30:39.944 --> 02:30:41.878
Frodo?

1278
02:30:48.986 --> 02:30:51.546
I know why you seek solitude.

1279
02:30:52.290 --> 02:30:55.691
You suffer. I see it day by day.

1280
02:30:56.494 --> 02:30:59.554
You sure you do not suffer needlessly?

1281
02:31:01.132 --> 02:31:03.794
There are other ways. Frodo.

1282
02:31:04.001 --> 02:31:07.835
- Other paths that we might take.
- I know what you would say.

1283
02:31:08.039 --> 02:31:11.839
It would seem like wisdom
but for the warning in my heart.

1284
02:31:12.043 --> 02:31:15.137
Warning? Against what?

1285
02:31:15.346 --> 02:31:17.473
We're all afraid. Frodo.

1286
02:31:17.682 --> 02:31:21.311
But to let that fear drive us.
to destroy what hope we have...

1287
02:31:21.519 --> 02:31:25.319
...don't you see that is madness?
- There is no other way.

1288
02:31:27.058 --> 02:31:30.425
I ask only for the strength
to defend my people!

1289
02:31:31.996 --> 02:31:34.021
- Lf you would but lend me the Ring.
- No.

1290
02:31:35.266 --> 02:31:38.963
- Why do you recoil? I am no thief.
- You are not yourself.

1291
02:31:40.738 --> 02:31:44.071
What chance do you think you have?

1292
02:31:44.308 --> 02:31:48.972
They will find you.
They will take the Ring.

1293
02:31:49.180 --> 02:31:52.877
And you will beg for death
before the end!

1294
02:31:55.019 --> 02:31:57.078
You fool!

1295
02:31:57.288 --> 02:32:01.281
It is not yours. save by unhappy chance!
It could have been mine.

1296
02:32:01.492 --> 02:32:04.290
It should be mine! Give it to me!

1297
02:32:04.495 --> 02:32:05.757
- Give it to me!
- No!

1298
02:32:05.963 --> 02:32:07.794
- Give it to me!
- No.

1299
02:32:15.440 --> 02:32:17.499
I see your mind.

1300
02:32:17.708 --> 02:32:20.677
You will take the Ring to Sauron!

1301
02:32:20.878 --> 02:32:22.743
You will betray us!

1302
02:32:22.947 --> 02:32:26.144
You'll go to your death.
and the death of us all!

1303
02:32:26.584 --> 02:32:30.247
Curse you!
Curse you and all the halflings!

1304
02:32:37.295 --> 02:32:38.819
Frodo?

1305
02:32:43.134 --> 02:32:44.726
Frodo.

1306
02:32:48.639 --> 02:32:50.698
What have I done?

1307
02:32:50.908 --> 02:32:52.603
Please. Frodo.

1308
02:32:52.810 --> 02:32:55.472
Frodo. I'm sorry!

1309
02:33:44.061 --> 02:33:45.494
Frodo?

1310
02:33:46.764 --> 02:33:49.824
- It has taken Boromir.
- Where is the Ring?

1311
02:33:50.034 --> 02:33:51.831
Stay away!

1312
02:33:52.270 --> 02:33:53.828
Frodo!

1313
02:33:56.107 --> 02:33:59.907
- I swore to protect you.
- Can you protect me from yourself?

1314
02:34:09.620 --> 02:34:12.111
Would you destroy it?

1315
02:34:17.061 --> 02:34:19.029
Aragorn.

1316
02:34:22.433 --> 02:34:24.765
Aragorn.

1317
02:34:26.571 --> 02:34:28.436
Elessar.

1318
02:34:36.080 --> 02:34:39.447
I would have gone with you to the end.

1319
02:34:40.151 --> 02:34:42.984
Into the very fires of Mordor.

1320
02:34:46.290 --> 02:34:47.484
I know.

1321
02:34:49.927 --> 02:34:55.388
Look after the others. Especially Sam.
He will not understand.

1322
02:34:59.170 --> 02:35:00.865
Go. Frodo!

1323
02:35:03.874 --> 02:35:05.364
Run.

1324
02:35:05.610 --> 02:35:07.271
Run!

1325
02:35:31.836 --> 02:35:33.531
Mr. Frodo!

1326
02:35:42.780 --> 02:35:44.577
Find the halfling!

1327
02:35:46.183 --> 02:35:48.743
Find the halfling!

1328
02:35:52.189 --> 02:35:53.884
Elendil!

1329
02:36:00.398 --> 02:36:01.922
Aragorn. go!

1330
02:36:23.654 --> 02:36:24.951
Frodo!

1331
02:36:25.523 --> 02:36:27.150
Hide here. Quick!

1332
02:36:27.792 --> 02:36:29.225
Come on!

1333
02:36:31.696 --> 02:36:33.755
What's he doing?

1334
02:36:37.968 --> 02:36:39.959
He's leaving.

1335
02:36:44.742 --> 02:36:47.677
- No!
- Pippin!

1336
02:36:52.616 --> 02:36:54.914
Run. Frodo. Go on!

1337
02:36:55.486 --> 02:36:58.580
- Hey! Hey. you!
- Over here!

1338
02:36:58.989 --> 02:37:00.581
- Over here!
- This way!

1339
02:37:11.469 --> 02:37:13.767
- It's working!
- I know it's working! Run!

1340
02:38:03.187 --> 02:38:06.247
- The horn of Gondor.
- Boromir.

1341
02:38:31.081 --> 02:38:32.207
Run!

1342
02:41:51.415 --> 02:41:53.007
No.

1343
02:41:56.787 --> 02:41:59.813
- They took the little ones.
- Hold still.

1344
02:42:00.090 --> 02:42:02.115
Frodo. Where is Frodo?

1345
02:42:03.994 --> 02:42:05.461
I let Frodo go.

1346
02:42:06.130 --> 02:42:08.758
Then you did what I could not.

1347
02:42:09.733 --> 02:42:13.032
I tried to take the Ring from him.

1348
02:42:13.604 --> 02:42:17.836
- The Ring is beyond our reach now.
- Forgive me.

1349
02:42:18.042 --> 02:42:20.340
I did not see it.

1350
02:42:20.544 --> 02:42:23.741
- I have failed you all.
- No. Boromir.

1351
02:42:24.515 --> 02:42:26.710
You fought bravely.

1352
02:42:27.251 --> 02:42:29.685
You have kept your honor.

1353
02:42:30.320 --> 02:42:32.185
Leave it.

1354
02:42:32.656 --> 02:42:34.624
It is over.

1355
02:42:35.826 --> 02:42:41.025
The world of Men will fall.
And all will come to darkness...

1356
02:42:41.498 --> 02:42:44.490
...and my city to ruin.

1357
02:42:48.739 --> 02:42:51.606
I do not know what strength
is in my blood...

1358
02:42:51.809 --> 02:42:55.472
...but I swear to you.
I will not let the White City fall...

1359
02:42:56.447 --> 02:42:58.972
...nor our people fail.

1360
02:42:59.917 --> 02:43:01.316
Our people.

1361
02:43:05.155 --> 02:43:07.214
Our people.

1362
02:43:28.979 --> 02:43:32.005
I would have followed you. my brother.

1363
02:43:33.550 --> 02:43:35.541
My captain.

1364
02:43:38.155 --> 02:43:40.089
My king.

1365
02:43:59.743 --> 02:44:01.973
Be at peace...

1366
02:44:02.379 --> 02:44:04.347
...son of Gondor.

1367
02:44:43.487 --> 02:44:45.250
Frodo!

1368
02:45:04.808 --> 02:45:08.073
I wish the Ring had never come to me.

1369
02:45:09.346 --> 02:45:12.338
I wish none of this had happened.

1370
02:45:15.319 --> 02:45:18.083
So do all who live
to see such times...

1371
02:45:18.288 --> 02:45:21.746
...but that is not for them to decide.

1372
02:45:21.959 --> 02:45:24.553
All you have to decide...

1373
02:45:24.761 --> 02:45:29.528
...is what to do with the time
that is given to you.

1374
02:45:58.362 --> 02:46:00.421
Frodo. no!

1375
02:46:00.897 --> 02:46:02.194
Frodo!

1376
02:46:02.966 --> 02:46:05.628
- Mr. Frodo!
- No. Sam.

1377
02:46:09.206 --> 02:46:11.174
Go back. Sam!

1378
02:46:11.675 --> 02:46:15.236
- I'm going to Mordor alone.
- Of course you are.

1379
02:46:15.445 --> 02:46:18.278
And I'm coming with you!

1380
02:46:18.749 --> 02:46:21.149
You can't swim!

1381
02:46:24.955 --> 02:46:26.650
Sam!

1382
02:46:32.262 --> 02:46:33.593
Sam!

1383
02:47:14.504 --> 02:47:17.234
I made a promise. Mr. Frodo.

1384
02:47:17.574 --> 02:47:21.908
A promise:
"Don't you leave him. Samwise Gamgee."

1385
02:47:23.013 --> 02:47:25.641
And I don't mean to.

1386
02:47:25.882 --> 02:47:28.077
I don't mean to.

1387
02:47:29.753 --> 02:47:31.550
Sam.

1388
02:47:46.470 --> 02:47:48.131
Come on.

1389
02:48:16.833 --> 02:48:21.133
Hurry! Frodo and Sam
have reached the eastern shore.

1390
02:48:36.219 --> 02:48:41.020
- You mean not to follow them.
- Frodo's fate is no longer in our hands.

1391
02:48:44.428 --> 02:48:49.297
Then it has all been in vain.
The Fellowship has failed.

1392
02:49:01.178 --> 02:49:04.341
Not if we hold true to each other.

1393
02:49:05.882 --> 02:49:10.182
We will not abandon Merry and Pippin
to torment and death.

1394
02:49:11.154 --> 02:49:16.421
Not while we have strength left.
Leave all that can be spared behind.

1395
02:49:17.928 --> 02:49:19.919
We travel light.

1396
02:49:20.130 --> 02:49:21.825
Let us hunt some Orc.

1397
02:49:25.068 --> 02:49:26.831
Yes!

1398
02:49:46.056 --> 02:49:47.284
Mordor.

1399
02:49:47.924 --> 02:49:51.291
I hope the others find a safer road.

1400
02:49:52.229 --> 02:49:54.789
Strider will look after them.

1401
02:49:55.732 --> 02:49:59.099
I don't suppose
we'll ever see them again.

1402
02:49:59.436 --> 02:50:01.836
We may yet. Mr. Frodo.

1403
02:50:02.038 --> 02:50:03.630
We may.

1404
02:50:05.675 --> 02:50:06.767
Sam...

1405
02:50:10.347 --> 02:50:12.975
...I'm glad you are with me.

1406
02:50:13.305 --> 02:51:13.303
